"approach\":\"Monolithic Rust visual-analysis worker before measurement\",\"reason\":\"It couples independent features and release boundaries without proven compute residency.\"}],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"q-visual-analysis-practicality\",\"kind\":\"QUESTION\",\"label\":\"Practical visual analysis features\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-dom-layout-plane\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"DOM already supplies layout geometry\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-scre... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n{\"type\":\"iteration_start\",\"iteration\":7,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T04:59:21.490Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":7,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.74,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This iteration separated offline/privacy value from implementation language, established the installed ONNX stack as the mandatory local multimodal oracle, distinguished ort from Candle by parity and packaging risk, and converted Rust adoption into worker-isolation and artifact-contract gates at 10x/100x scale.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Assess on-device local text and image embedding models through Rust runtimes such as ONNX Runtime or Candle: capability, model residency, packaging, privacy/offline value, JS/native-addon alternatives, and current/10x/100x gates.\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Does local text/image inference require Rust?\",\"Which Rust runtime is the default candidate?\",\"Should a resident model use an addon or sidecar?\",\"What clears the current, 10x, and 100x runtime gates?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Rust as privacy or offline enabler\",\"reason\":\"Locality follows model provisioning and network policy, not host language.\"},{\"approach\":\"Rust ort rewrite for inference speed\",\"reason\":\"Node and Rust wrappers execute the same native ONNX Runtime kernels.\"},{\"approach\":\"In-process native addon as default model host\",\"reason\":\"It adds no kernel residency and loses sidecar crash and RSS isolation.\"},{\"approach\":\"Bundle model weights in npm or native binary\",\"reason\":\"Weights are large, licensed, profile-specific artifacts with an independent lifecycle.\"},{\"approach\":\"Candle as universal runtime\",\"reason\":\"Each model architecture, preprocessing path, backend, and numerical contract requires separate qualification.\"}],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"q-local-model-rust-gate\",\"kind\":\"QUESTION\",\"label\":\"Rust gate for local text and image models\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-ts-ort-local-baseline\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n{\"type\":\"iteration_start\",\"iteration\":8,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T05:05:08.853Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":8,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.71,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This iteration found the cross-generation parsed-projection cache as the real missing capability, measured current hashing cost, isolated the safe bounded pre-transaction worker seam, and proved that watcher correctness and external-artifact publication are separate contracts.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Assess content-addressed caches, incremental hashing, parallel streaming corpus indexing, and a Rust file watcher for automatic reindex.\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which indexing automations materially benefit from Rust today?\",\"Is a new content-addressed cache useful?\",\"Does a Rust watcher improve correctness?\",\"Where must atomicity remain?\",\"What is the scale gate?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Replace existing content identities with a Rust cache\",\"reason\":\"Aggregate, retrieval, generation, and embedding content identities already exist; only cross-generation parsed-projection reuse is missing.\"},{\"approach\":\"Replace canonical SHA-256 with BLAKE3\",\"reason\":\"Current hashing is not material at present scale and the change would break persisted identity and oracle parity.\"},{\"approach\":\"Parallel SQLite publication\",\"reason\":\"The single transaction is the correctness boundary; bounded parallelism belongs in verification and parsing.\"},{\"approach\":\"Watcher as freshness authority\",\"reason\":\"Node, Chokidar, and Rust notify all consume fallible platform events, so authoritative reconciliation remains required.\"},{\"approach\":\"Standalone Rust watcher at current scale\",\"reason\":\"Chokidar provides normalized atomic and chunked-write handling without a new binary lifecycle.\"}],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"q-index-automation-scale\",\"kind\":\"QUESTION\",\"label\":\"Index automation by scale\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-projection-cache-ga... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n{\"type\":\"iteration_start\",\"iteration\":9,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T05:10:01.528Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":9,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.58,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This iteration proved that candidate caps decouple RRF cost from corpus growth, identified the current test oracle's exact parity gaps, and made adapter selection derivative of an independently material resident or unbounded workload.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Pressure-test deterministic ranking kernels, reusable pure-core boundaries, and TS-oracle parity across napi-rs/WASM/sidecar choices.\",\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"q-deterministic-core-materiality\",\"kind\":\"QUESTION\",\"label\":\"Deterministic Rust core materiality\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"RRF cost is candidate bounded\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-oracle-not-byte-complete\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"Current oracle lacks byte parity\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-adapter-follows-residency\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"Adapter follows owner workload residency\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"c-kernel-supporting-only\",\"kind\":\"CLAIM\",\"label\":\"Deterministic kernel is supporting infrastructure\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"s-retrieval-rrf-bound\",\"kind\":\"SOURCE\",\"label\":\"Styles retrieval candidate and fusion contract\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"s-retrieval-test-oracle\",\"kind\":\"SOURCE\",\"label\":\"Styles weighted RRF test\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"s-rust-parity-standard\",\"kind\":\"SOURCE\",\"label\":\"Rust differential parity standard\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-bounded-answers-materiality\",\"source\":\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\",\"target\":\"q-deterministic-core-materiality\",\"relation\":\"ANSWERS\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-bounded-supports-supporting\",\"source\":\"f-rrf-candidate-bounded\",\"target\":\"c-kernel-supporting-only\",\"relation\":\"SUPPORTS\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-residency-supports-supporting\",\"source\":\"f-adapter-follows-residency\",\"target\":\"c-kernel-supporting-only\",\"relation\":\"SUPPORTS\"},{\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n{\"type\":\"iteration_start\",\"iteration\":10,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T05:13:51.347Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":10,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.46,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This final iteration converted nine evidence rounds into one ranked gate matrix, made the multi-artifact manifest and oracle the unconditional first phase, and separated worthwhile capability work from conditional Rust residency.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Adjudicate and rank the complete opportunity set, identify not-worth-Rust calls, and define phased adoption preserving TypeScript ownership and pinned-oracle parity.\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which vector-search architecture unlocks capability at 1x, 10x, and 100x?\",\"Which indexing and embedding automations materially benefit from Rust?\",\"Which visual and multimodal features are practical?\",\"Is a shared Rust search core worthwhile?\",\"Which opportunities clear residency, materiality, and scale gates?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Like-for-like Rust ownership transfers\",\"reason\":\"Ranking, hashing, caching, watching, SQLite publication, and full indexing either already run natively or add no new capability.\"},{\"approach\":\"Three-system shared Rust search platform\",\"reason\":\"Code graph has no vector workload and the two retrieval systems have incompatible policy and publication contracts.\"},{\"approach\":\"Custom ANN before measured 100x gates\",\"reason\":\"Maintained exact and HNSW candidates plus bounded SQL eligibility must be exhausted first.\"},{\"approach\":\"Query-visible external artifacts outside the generation manifest\",\"reason\":\"They cannot be atomically bound to the authoritative SQLite generation.\"}],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"q-final-rust-opportunity-verdict\",\"kind\":\"QUESTION\",\"label\":\"Final Rust opportunity verdict\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-manifest-oracle-first\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"Manifest and TS oracle come first\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-no-rust-clears... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_synthesis_deferred\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"reason\":\"detached lineage scope permits writes only inside fanout lineage artifact directory\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T05:22:59.813Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-opencode-1784520993412-ps7omk\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"totalIterations\":10,\"answeredCount\":0,\"totalQuestions\":5,\"adjudicatedCount\":5,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T05:22:59.813Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-opencode-1784520993412-ps7omk\",\"generation\":1}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\".opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/.deep-research.lock\",\"releasePhase\":\"synthesis\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-20T05:24:24.842Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":34,"totalLines":34,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/013-styles-database-rust-opportunities/research/lineages/sol-opencode/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1784616134093,"end":1784616134189}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e55e3c0bf11150f016a5f14c5cb988191bb5207dbaf273a7f"}},"id":"prt_f836925ca001GerMQC2Q9ZB782","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f8368c0e7001D1i4allOODIHEM"}}
