{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784616173923,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_YGKReCy4IDwncax83Uo6c7s9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"kebab-case|Kebab-Case Canon","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-doc","include":"filesystem-naming-convention.md"},"output":"Found 6 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md:\n  Line 2: title: Filesystem Naming Convention - Kebab-Case Canon\n\n  Line 3: description: The single canonical rule that kebab-case is the sole in-scope filesystem-naming form, with the full exemption boundary and the identifier-versus-filename line.\n\n  Line 6:   - \"kebab-case naming rule\"\n\n  Line 14: # Filesystem Naming Convention - Kebab-Case Canon\n\n  Line 24: **In-scope filesystem names use kebab-case.** This covers directory names, file names, and script filenames.\n\n  Line 88: `core-standards.md` §2 currently documents the legacy snake_case filename rule, which the `validate_document.py` classifier still applies. That rule and the classifier are reconciled to this kebab-case canon during the consumer-migration and generator phases of the naming program, under bounded dual-name tolerance so every intermediate state stays green. Until then, this document states the target; `core-standards.md` §2 carries a forward pointer here. This document is the single canonical source that later phases reference instead of restating ad-hoc rules.\n","metadata":{"matches":6,"truncated":false},"title":"kebab-case|Kebab-Case Canon","time":{"start":1784616173875,"end":1784616173921}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f53d9d2f7e6540e016a5f14ed36808191a54a07a3602b0202"}},"id":"prt_f8369c0cf001rTrjHS3JjjCbRe","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f83696abf001OHKQV928Z1SHm0"}}
