{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784616200921,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_d8Vq03aZbqgVM1K1TWb54oVy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"import .*styles|from ['\"].*styles|_engine|_db|_harness|_manifest|_retrieval-manifest","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design","include":"*.{mjs,js,ts,json,md}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:\n  Line 74: Style-library retrieval can run through the `legacy`, `shadow`, or `persistent` adapter in `styles/_engine/`. It defaults to `legacy`, so the flat files remain authoritative. The opt-in persistent backend under `styles/_db/` uses SQLite and FTS5 with a rebuildable vector projection, an incremental `DISCOVER` through `PUBLISH` indexer, and eligibility-first weighted-RRF retrieval.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:\n  Line 215:   styles/_engine/        # legacy|shadow|persistent retrieval adapter (default: legacy)\n\n  Line 216:   styles/_db/            # SQLite + FTS5 persistent index and rebuildable vectors\n\n  Line 226: Style-library retrieval passes through the `legacy|shadow|persistent` adapter under `styles/_engine/`. The adapter defaults to `legacy`, and the flat style files remain authoritative. When explicitly enabled, the persistent backend under `styles/_db/` provides SQLite and FTS5 storage, a rebuildable vector projection, an incremental `DISCOVER` to `PUBLISH` indexer, and eligibility-first weighted-RRF retrieval across structured, FTS5, and vector lanes.\n\n  Line 261: - Style retrieval: `styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs` (mode switch, default `legacy`) and `styles/_db/README.md` (persistent index lifecycle).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/tests/corpus-baseline-v3.test.ts:\n  Line 19: const MANIFEST_PATH = path.resolve(__dirname, '../../../styles/_retrieval-manifest.json');\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:\n  Line 60:   '_engine',\n\n  Line 66:   '_retrieval-manifest.json',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/style-database-backend.md:\n  Line 18: The styles library includes a persistent retrieval backend under `styles/_db/`. It stores a versioned style index in SQLite with FTS5 and maintains a rebuildable vector projection without making the database the source of truth.\n\n  Line 20: The adapter under `styles/_engine/` supports `legacy`, `shadow` and `persistent` modes. It defaults to `legacy`, so flat style files remain authoritative and persistent reads require explicit opt-in.\n\n  Line 32: An operator surface under `styles/_db/operator.mjs` exposes the persistent-path lifecycle as documented entry points — status, build, cutover, rollback and vector-repair — and enforces a current-plus-rollback generation retention invariant so published generation files are pruned safely without dropping the live generation or its rollback target. Enabling the persistent path remains a separate operator decision.\n\n  Line 42: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs` | Storage | Defines the versioned SQLite, FTS5, vector, relationship and generation schema. |\n\n  Line 43: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs` | Indexer | Runs the incremental generation lifecycle and atomic publish. |\n\n  Line 44: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs` | Retrieval | Applies eligibility-first structured, FTS5 and vector weighted-RRF ranking. |\n\n  Line 45: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/vectors.mjs` | Projection | Maintains the non-blocking rebuildable vector queue and cache. |\n\n  Line 46: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs` | Adapter | Selects `legacy`, `shadow` or `persistent` and defaults to `legacy`. |\n\n  Line 47: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs` | Facade | Routes the existing style-library surface through the adapter. |\n\n  Line 48: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs` | Operator | Persistent status/build/cutover/rollback/vector-repair with current-plus-rollback generation retention. |\n\n  Line 54: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/schema.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers database schema behavior. |\n\n  Line 55: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/indexer.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers indexing and generation publication. |\n\n  Line 56: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/retrieval.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers indexed retrieval and rank fusion. |\n\n  Line 57: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/adapter.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers adapter modes and the legacy default. |\n\n  Line 58: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/operator.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers the operator lifecycle and current-plus-rollback retention. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/styles-library-utilization/retrieval-engine.md:\n  Line 42: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs` | Script | Exposes build, query and hydrate commands. |\n\n  Line 43: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs` | Adapter | Selects `legacy`, `shadow` or `persistent`; defaults to `legacy`. |\n\n  Line 44: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/eligibility.mjs` | Shared | Decides deterministic membership before ranking. |\n\n  Line 45: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs` | Shared | Enforces live-record, generation, path and byte guards. |\n\n  Line 46: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/corpus-use-proof.mjs` | Shared | Validates manifest-bound corpus-use proof. |\n\n  Line 52: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/eligibility-first.test.mjs` | Automated test | Proves ranking cannot reintroduce an ineligible record. |\n\n  Line 53: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/hydrate-guard.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers generation mismatch, poisoned records and path escape. |\n\n  Line 54: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/proof.test.mjs` | Automated test | Covers proof binding and ready-gate refusal. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:\n  Line 28: import { runHydrate, runQuery } from '../../styles/_engine/style-library.mjs';\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/comparison-lane.test.mjs:\n  Line 16: import { loadManifest } from '../../../styles/_engine/manifest.mjs';\n\n  Line 17: import { runBuild } from '../../../styles/_engine/style-library.mjs';\n\n  Line 23: } from '../../../styles/_engine/__tests__/fixtures.mjs';\n\n  Line 61:   const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n\n  Line 108:   const crawlManifestPath = path.join(corpusRoot, '_manifest.json');\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-01