 tests additionally bind module paths, manifests, and fixture roots; `_engine` and `_db` have bidirectional dependencies. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-29]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n-[None yet]\n+- Exact path/import searches plus focused reads separated executable migration blockers from documentation-only references. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n-[None yet]\n+- Broad repository path searches were dominated by historical specs and generated research, so they are unsuitable as the implementation checklist without scope filtering. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n-[No exhausted approach categories yet]\n+### Independent subtree moves -- BLOCKED (iteration 1)\n+- `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` cannot be treated as unrelated rename units because manifests are root-bound and engine/database imports are bidirectional.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n-[None yet]\n+- Independent `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` moves without a shared path plan: internal imports and root-derived constants would break. (iteration 1)\n+- Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies: update executable consumers first, documentation second. (iteration 1)\n+- Commands and agents as direct path blockers: scoped exact searches found no current matches. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n@@ -60,14 +62,16 @@\n <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n-[None yet]\n+- How should committed crawl/retrieval manifests be divided between authoritative corpus metadata and runtime publication metadata? (iteration 1)\n+- Should engine and database modules become sibling domains under one `lib/` boundary to remove the artificial subtree cycle? (iteration 1)\n+- Which path constants must become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations? (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Map the exact current styles-tree topology and all path consumers before proposing names.\n+Compare the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` ownership boundaries with the mapped styles topology, identifying what transfers directly and what must intentionally differ for authoritative corpus data, committed manifests, and opt-in runtime databases.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n","additions":12,"deletions":8},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lin