 policy should implementation use?\n+Carried-Forward Open Questions:\n+- How should crawl and retrieval manifests divide authoritative corpus metadata from runtime publication metadata?\n+- Should engine and database modules become sibling domains under one lib boundary?\n+- Which path constants should become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations?\n+Last 3 Iterations Summary: run 1: topology and path consumers (0.89).\n+Pivot Lineage: none yet.\n+Saturated Directions: independent engine/database/harness moves without a shared path plan; commands/agents as direct path consumers.\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Registry: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+- Write iteration narrative to: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+- Write delta to: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- You are the `deep-research` LEAF agent for exactly one iteration. Read `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md`, then config, state, strategy, registry, and iteration 1 before research.\n+- Do not dispatch sub-