ta under `styles/`]\\n \\n ## Ruled Out\\n \\n\",\"additions\":1,\"deletions\":1}],\"diagnostics\":{},\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"Success. Updated the following files:\\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-002.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784616985174,\"end\":1784616985177}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_0643b102786d06d3016a5f181290288191bd4f3d80380aa149\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f83760962001gsjAwzJLPI4lOi\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f8375e5370013Iosc7zatDiF6t\"}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784616985655,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f837624350010q5s7FLs7RAuek\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f8375e5370013Iosc7zatDiF6t\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":104187,\"input\":5706,\"output\":386,\"reasoning\":303,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":97792}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784616990405,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f837636c4001nqTPZFry6QRKon\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f837625f60010dLenOO9o28JfH\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"snapshot\":\"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784616999810,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_sMRiT4FOhie2qYMfVthqLeIN\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"node -e 'const fs=require(\\\"fs\\\"); const root=\\\".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast\\\"; const narrative=fs.readFileSync(`${root}/iterations/iteration-002.md`,\\\"utf8\\\"); const state=fs.readFileSync(`${root}/deep-research-state.jsonl`,\\\"utf8\\\").trim().split(\\\"\\\\n\\\"); const delta=fs.readFileSync(`${root}/deltas/iter-002.jsonl`,\\\"utf8\\\").trim().split(\\\"\\\\n\\\"); for(const line of [...state,...delta]) JSON.parse(line); const record=state.filter(line=>JSON.parse(line).type===\\\"iteration\\\"&&JSON.parse(line).iteration===2); if(record.length!==1) throw new Error(`iteration-2 state count ${record.length}`); if(record[0]!==delta[0]) throw new Error(\\\"canonical state/delta records differ\\\"); for(const section of [\\\"## Focus\\\",\\\"## Findings\\\",\\\"## Sources Consulted\\\",\\\"## Assessment\\\",\\\"## Reflection\\\",\\\"## Recommended Next Focus\\\"]) if(!narrative.includes(section)) throw new Error(`missing ${section}`); const findings=narrative.split(\\\"## Findings\\\\n\\\\n\\\")[1].split(\\\"\\\\n\\\\n## Ruled Out\\\")[0].split(\\\"\\\\n\\\").filter(line=>/^\\\\d+\\\\./.test(line)); if(findings.length!==8||findings.some(line=>!line.includes(\\\"[SOURCE:\\\")&&!line.includes(\\\"[INFERENCE:\\\"))) throw new Error(\\\"finding citation check failed\\\"); console.log(JSON.stringify({iterationFile:true,stateIterationAppendCount:record.length,deltaCanonicalMatch:true,jsonlValid:true,findings:findings.length,citationsComplete:true,reducerOwnedFilesTouched:false,packetBoundaryRespected:true}));'\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research\"},\"output\":\"{\\\"iterationFile\\\":true,\\\"stateIterationAppendCount\\\":1,\\\"deltaCanonicalMatch\\\":true,\\\"jsonlValid\\\":true,\\\"findings\\\":8,\\\"citationsComplete\\\":true,\\\"reducerOwnedFilesTouched\\\":false,\\\"packetBoundaryRespected\\\":true}\\n\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"{\\\"iterationFile\\\":true,\\\"stateIterationAppendCount\\\":1,\\\"deltaCanonicalMatch\\\":true,\\\"jsonlValid\\\":true,\\\"findings\\\":8,\\\"citationsComplete\\\":true,\\\"reducerOwnedFilesTouched\\\":false,\\\"packetBoundaryRespected\\\":true}\\n\",\"exit\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"node -e 'const fs=require(\\\"fs\\\"); const root=\\\".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast\\\"; const narrative=fs.readFileSync(`${root}/iterations/iteration-002.md`,\\\"utf8\\\"); const state=fs.readFileSync(`${root}/deep-research-state.jsonl`,\\\"utf8\\\").trim().split(\\\"\\\\n\\\"); const delta=fs.readFileSync(`${root}/deltas/iter-002.jsonl`,\\\"utf8\\\").trim().split(\\\"\\\\n\\\"); for(const line of [...state,...delta]) JSON.parse(line); const record=state.filter(line=>JSON.parse(line).type===\\\"iteration\\\"&&JSON.parse(line).iteration===2); if(record.length!==1) throw new Error(`iteration-2 state count ${record.length}`); if(record[0]!==delta[0]) throw new Error(\\\"canonical state/delta records differ\\\"); for(const section of [\\\"## Focus\\\",\\\"## Findings\\\",\\\"## Sources Consulted\\\",\\\"## Assessment\\\",\\\"## Reflection\\\",\\\"## Recommended Next Focus\\\"]) if(!narrative.includes(section)) throw new Error(`missing ${section}`); const findings=narrative.split(\\\"## Findings\\\\n\\\\n\\\")[1].split(\\\"\\\\n\\\\n## Ruled Out\\\")[0].split(\\\"\\\\n\\\").filter(line=>/^\\\\d+\\\\./.test(line)); if(findings.length!==8||findings.some(line=>!line.includes(\\\"[SOURCE:\\\")&&!line.includes(\\\"[INFERENCE:\\\"))) throw new Error(\\\"finding citation check failed\\\"); console.log(JSON.stringify({iterationFile:true,stateIterationAppendCount:record.length,deltaCanonicalMatch:true,jsonlValid:true,findings:findings.length,citationsComplete:true,reducerOwnedFilesTouched:false,packetBoundaryRespected:true}));'\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784616999807,\"end\":1784616999809}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_00679e8294b9dbfd016a5f181ff67c8191b0b0d77322575eac\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f83763cf6001fK43RPcxxnCamZ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f837625f60010dLenOO9o28JfH\"}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784617000291,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f83765d610010dnIsEBW5TEHWe\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f837625f60010dLenOO9o28JfH\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":104764,\"input\":1337,\"output\":454,\"reasoning\":61,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":102912}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784617002269,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f8376651a00155Mu6DIahXUonr\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83765f1e001IkSG2EcBdkkAIs\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"snapshot\":\"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784617004690,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f8376651c001SCn46xxLfmB4xk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83765f1e001IkSG2EcBdkkAIs\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"## Iteration 2 Complete\\n\\n**Focus:** Runtime transfer rules and styles-specific differences  \\n**Findings:** 8 findings, `newInfoRatio: 0.88`  \\n**Question answered:** Which runtime boundaries transfer directly, and where styles should differ  \\n**Next focus:** Concrete kebab-case target layout\\n\\n**Artifacts written:**\\n- `iterations/iteration-002.md`\\n- `deltas/iter-002.jsonl`\\n- `deep-research-state.jsonl` appended once\\n\\nVerification passed: valid JSONL, canonical state/delta records match, all findings cited, and reducer-owned files untouched.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784617002268,\"end\":1784617004689},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0dd605937bae8497016a5f182a39cc8191b0c2e21c7438e837\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784617005138,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f83767050001gS9v2qEECE96p2\",\"reason\":\"stop\",\"snapshot\":\"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83765f1e001IkSG2EcBdkkAIs\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8cfe3dffezVJT82nrpKM7g5\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":104955,\"input\":890,\"output\":129,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":103936}},\"cost\":0}}\n","exit":0,"truncated":true,"outputPath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f83735d40001DWCdkEBW7F2ndh"},"title":"env -i HOME=\"$HOME\" PATH=\"$PATH\" LANG=\"$LANG\" TMPDIR=\"$TMPDIR\" USER=\"$USER\" LOGNAME=\"$LOGNAME\" OPENAI_API_KEY=\"${OPENAI_API_KEY:-}\" AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0 opencode run --model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir \"$PWD\" \"$(<'.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-002.md')\" </dev/null","time":{"start":1784617005139,"end":1784617005716}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_083044d2df3046a8016a5f174b750c81919815dc4c06dfc0da"}},"id":"prt_f8372fed50014AHXvj2Vb7f7mt","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f8372c772001PRKIV2knCCW1LU"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784617006181,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"id":"prt_f83767462001AB45yq47dNSlQD","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0","messageID":"msg_f8372c772001PRKIV2knCCW1LU","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":275688,"input":1564,"output":197,"reasoning":7,"cache":{"write":0,"read":273920}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784617009721,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"id":"prt_f83768237001r2NONs4AYhLGqj","messageID":"msg_f83767612001jB3wO11nDnllql","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","snapshot":"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784617015094,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kS1BbUWC8m5LPPQWehZT2DVJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-002.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-002.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 2: Reference-Architecture Transfer Rules and Styles-Specific Differences\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: \n5: Compare the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` ownership boundaries with the mapped styles topology. The selected interpretation is architectural transfer rules, not a final target-tree or migration sequence; those remain separate later-iteration questions.\n6: \n7: ## Actions Taken\n8: \n9: 1. Inspected the reference runtime's `lib/`, `scripts/`, `database/`, tests, and path-resolution seams.\n10: 2. Compared those boundaries with the current styles engine, database, extraction harness, and manifest path ownership.\n11: 3. Classified corpus metadata, committed retrieval metadata, and mutable database publication metadata by authority and lifecycle.\n12: 4. Tested whether the reference package boundary and test setup transfer literally or only structurally.\n13: \n14: ## Findings\n15: \n16: 1. The runtime's primary transferable rule is a two-surface code boundary: importable implementation belongs under `lib/`, while executable adapters under `scripts/` parse inputs, call library functions, emit machine-readable output, and close resources. Styles currently combines both roles in `_engine/style-library.mjs` and places the operator CLI inside `_db`, so the transfer should split thin query/build/operator entry points from reusable engine/database modules rather than merely renaming `_engine` and `_db`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:117-121] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:1-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:69-80]\n17: 2. Engine and database should become sibling domains inside one `lib/` boundary, not separate top-level backends. The existing persistent adapter imports database retrieval/schema while the database retrieval path depends back on engine card assembly, so one library boundary acknowledges the real coupling while domain subdirectories preserve ownership. This transfers the runtime's `lib/deep-loop`, `lib/coverage-graph`, and `lib/council` pattern without copying those domain names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:109-115] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:9-18] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:21]\n18: 3. A top-level `database/` boundary transfers directly only for mutable runtime publication state: the logical SQLite path, immutable generation files, `.current.json` pointer, rollback generation, locks, and transient sidecars belong together there. It must not absorb source modules or authoritative corpus inputs. The reference runtime creates SQLite state on demand and excludes transient sidecars, while styles already models its database as a rebuildable projection with atomic generation publication and rollback. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-30] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:3-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:40-49] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-10]\n19: 4. Styles intentionally needs a first-class authoritative corpus boundary that runtime does not have. The flat bundles remain the source of truth, persistent reads are a projection, and the indexer reads the crawl manifest from the same corpus ownership context before discovering bundle directories. Therefore the 1,290 bundle folders and corpus-authoritative metadata must move as one data domain, outside `lib/`, `scripts/`, and `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:1-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:645-663] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:16-18]\n20: 5. The three manifest classes divide by lifecycle rather than by file extension. The crawl manifest records authoritative extraction/provenance state and is written by the corpus acquisition script; the retrieval manifest is a committed, deterministic index derived from corpus data and used by the default legacy backend; database generation manifests are mutable publication pointers for opt-in persistent artifacts. The first two belong with corpus-owned committed metadata, while `.current.json` and generation manifests belong under `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:19-28,41-45] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-34] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-109] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:6-15,134-147]\n21: 6. Path ownership should transfer as an explicit library seam, but styles should improve on the reference's remaining positional derivation. Runtime exposes a canonical artifact-root import seam and exports its database directory from the database owner; styles currently derives corpus, manifest, and database locations independently from each module's parent directory. A single styles path module should export the styles root, corpus root, committed manifest paths, and database root, while callable APIs retain explicit path overrides for fixtures and external callers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:3-19] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:143-155] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:31-36,80-94] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-32] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:41-45]\n22: 7. A centralized `tests/` boundary transfers structurally: runtime separates unit, integration, lifecycle, helpers, and fixtures and owns discovery through a root config. For styles, engine tests, database tests, oracle data, and mode-adapter integration tests should be classified under one test root, but golden oracle files remain test evidence rather than corpus data or runtime database artifacts. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/vitest.config.ts:1-25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/:scoped-inventory] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:89-124] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-21]\n23: 8. The runtime should not be copied as a literal npm-package template. It has a scoped `vitest.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, and `package-lock.json`, but the expected `runtime/package.json` was absent during this pass; the styles tree likewise has no local package metadata. The safe transfer is therefore ownership and verification boundaries, not an unsupported claim that styles should immediately become an independently installable package. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/vitest.config.ts:1-25] [INFERENCE: direct read of `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/package.json` returned file-not-found, and scoped glob found no package metadata under `styles/`]\n24: \n25: ## Ruled Out\n26: \n27: - Ruled out a literal mirror of runtime directory names: styles requires an authoritative corpus and committed corpus manifests that runtime does not own.\n28: - Ruled out placing `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` under `database/`: their authority and default-backend lifecycle differ from mutable SQLite publication pointers.\n29: - Ruled out separate top-level `engine/` and `database-code/` source domains: current bidirectional imports make one `lib/` boundary the more accurate ownership model.\n30: - Ruled out treating the runtime as proof that styles needs a standalone npm package: the reference package metadata is incomplete in the checked-in tree.\n31: \n32: ## Dead Ends\n33: \n34: - Copying `runtime/` mechanically is exhausted as a design direction; only its ownership rules are transferable.\n35: - Parent-directory derivation should not be preserved as a compatibility strategy because the restructure intentionally breaks the positional relationship it assumes.\n36: \n37: ## Edge Cases\n38: \n39: - Ambiguous input: \"aligned to runtime\" could mean literal topology or ownership semantics; this iteration selected ownership semantics because the prompt explicitly requires styles-specific differences.\n40: - Contradictory evidence: the runtime config describes a standalone `npm test` path, but no `runtime/package.json` was present. This limits package-boundary transfer but does not invalidate the observed directory/test ownership pattern.\n41: - Missing dependencies: `runtime/package.json` was absent; `package-lock.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `vitest.config.ts`, runtime documentation, and actual test layout were used as bounded fallback evidence.\n42: - Partial success: none; the transfer/difference question is answered, while exact target names and migration ordering were intentionally deferred.\n43: \n44: ## Sources Consulted\n45: \n46: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44,107-146,191-229`\n47: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-30`\n48: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:143-155`\n49: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:3-19`\n50: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/vitest.config.ts:1-25`\n51: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/` scoped inventory\n52: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:1-36,73-109`\n53: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-34`\n54: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:9-18,52-56`\n55: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:1-147`\n56: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-32`\n57: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-32`\n58: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:645-663`\n59: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:19-28,41-45`\n60: \n61: ## Assessment\n62: \n63: - New information ratio: 0.88\n64: - Novelty justification: Six of eight transfer-rule findings are fully new and two refine iteration 1's preliminary runtime comparison and engine/database coupling.\n65: - Questions addressed: Which runtime ownership boundaries transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n66: - Questions answered: Which runtime ownership boundaries transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n67: - Confidence: High for code/data/database/manifest ownership; medium-high for package-boundary conclusions because the expected runtime package manifest is absent.\n68: - Status: complete\n69: \n70: ## Reflection\n71: \n72: - What worked and why: Comparing lifecycle and authority for each artifact class produced clearer transfer rules than matching directory names.\n73: - What did not work and why: Probing `runtime/package.json` failed because the file is absent, preventing a claim that the reference is a complete standalone npm package.\n74: - What I would do differently: The next pass should convert these ownership rules into one concrete kebab-case target tree and test each proposed location against all known path consumers.\n75: \n76: ## Recommended Next Focus\n77: \n78: Derive the concrete target tree from these rules, including exact homes for corpus bundles, committed corpus manifests, sibling `lib/engine` and `lib/database` domains, thin scripts, mutable database generations, centralized tests/fixtures/oracles, and documentation.\n\n(End of file - total 78 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 2: Reference-Architecture Transfer Rules and Styles-Specific Differences\n\n## Focus\n\nCompare the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` ownership boundaries with the mapped styles topology. The selected interpretation is architectural transfer rules, not a final target-tree or migration sequence; those remain separate later-iteration questions.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Inspected the reference runtime's `lib/`, `scripts/`, `database/`, tests, and path-resolution seams.\n2. Compared those boundaries with the current styles engine, database, extraction harness, and manifest path ownership.\n3. Classified corpus metadata, committed retrieval metadata, and mutable database publication metadata by authority and lifecycle.\n4. Tested whether the reference package boundary and test setup transfer literally or only structurally.\n\n## Findings\n\n1. The runtime's primary transferable rule is a two-surface code boundary: importable implementation belongs under `lib/`, while executable adapters under `scripts/` parse inputs, call library functions, emit machine-readable output, and close resources. Styles currently combines both roles in `_engine/style-library.mjs` and places the operator CLI inside `_db`, so the transfer should split thin query/build/operator entry points from reusable engine/database modules rather than merely renaming `_engine` and `_db`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:117-121] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:1-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:69-80]\n2. Engine and database should become sibling domains inside one `lib/` boundary, not separate top-level backends. The existing persistent adapter imports database retrieval/schema while the database retrieval path depends back on engine card assembly, so one library boundary acknowledges the real coupling while domain subdirectories preserve ownership. This transfers the runtime's `lib/deep-loop`, `lib/coverage-graph`, and `lib/council` pattern without copying those domain names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:109-115] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:9-18] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:21]\n3. A top-level `database/` boundary transfers directly only for mutable runtime publication state: the logical SQLite path, immutable generation files, `.current.json` pointer, rollback generation, locks, and transient sidecars belong together there. It must not absorb source modules or authoritative corpus inputs. The reference runtime creates SQLite state on demand and excludes transient sidecars, while styles already models its database as a rebuildable projection with atomic generation publication and rollback. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-30] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:3-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:40-49] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-10]\n4. Styles intentionally needs a first-class authoritative corpus boundary that runtime does not have. The flat bundles remain the source of truth, persistent reads are a projection, and the indexer reads the crawl manifest from the same corpus ownership context before discovering bundle directories. Therefore the 1,290 bundle folders and corpus-authoritative metadata must move as one data domain, outside `lib/`, `scripts/`, and `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:1-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:645-663] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:16-18]\n5. The three manifest classes divide by lifecycle rather than by file extension. The crawl manifest records authoritative extraction/provenance state and is written by the corpus acquisition script; the retrieval manifest is a committed, deterministic index derived from corpus data and used by the default legacy backend; database generation manifests are mutable publication pointers for opt-in persistent artifacts. The first two belong with corpus-owned committed metadata, while `.current.json` and generation manifests belong under `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:19-28,41-45] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-34] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-109] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:6-15,134-147]","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-002.md","text":"# Iteration 2: Reference-Architecture Transfer Rules and Styles-Specific Differences\n\n## Focus\n\nCompare the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` ownership boundaries with the mapped styles topology. The selected interpretation is architectural transfer rules, not a final target-tree or migration sequence; those remain separate later-iteration questions.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Inspected the reference runtime's `lib/`, `scripts/`, `database/`, tests, and path-resolution seams.\n2. Compared those boundaries with the current styles engine, database, extraction harness, and manifest path ownership.\n3. Classified corpus metadata, committed retrieval metadata, and mutable database publication metadata by authority and lifecycle.\n4. Tested whether the reference package boundary and test setup transfer literally or only structurally.\n\n## Findings\n\n1. The runtime's primary transferable rule is a two-surface code boundary: importable implementation belongs under `lib/`, while executable adapters under `scripts/` parse inputs, call library functions, emit machine-readable output, and close resources. Styles currently combines both roles in `_engine/style-library.mjs` and places the operator CLI inside `_db`, so the transfer should split thin query/build/operator entry points from reusable engine/database modules rather than merely renaming `_engine` and `_db`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:117-121] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:1-36] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:69-80]\n2. Engine and database should become sibling domains inside one `lib/` boundary, not separate top-level backends. The existing persistent adapter imports database retrieval/schema while the database retrieval path depends back on engine card assembly, so one library boundary acknowledges the real coupling while domain subdirectories preserve ownership. This transfers the runtime's `lib/deep-loop`, `lib/coverage-graph`, and `lib/council` pattern without copying those domain names. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:109-115] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:9-18] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:21]\n3. A top-level `database/` boundary transfers directly only for mutable runtime publication state: the logical SQLite path, immutable generation files, `.current.json` pointer, rollback generation, locks, and transient sidecars belong together there. It must not absorb source modules or authoritative corpus inputs. The reference runtime creates SQLite state on demand and excludes transient sidecars, while styles already models its database as a rebuildable projection with atomic generation publication and rollback. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-30] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:3-15] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:40-49] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-10]\n4. Styles intentionally needs a first-class authoritative corpus boundary that runtime does not have. The flat bundles remain the source of truth, persistent reads are a projection, and the indexer reads the crawl manifest from the same corpus ownership context before discovering bundle directories. Therefore the 1,290 bundle folders and corpus-authoritative metadata must move as one data domain, outside `lib/`, `scripts/`, and `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:1-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:645-663] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:16-18]\n5. The three manifest classes divide by lifecycle rather than by file extension. The crawl manifest records authoritative extraction/provenance state and is written by the corpus acquisition script; the retrieval manifest is a committed, deterministic index derived from corpus data and used by the default legacy backend; database generation manifests are mutable publication pointers for opt-in persistent artifacts. The first two belong with corpus-owned committed metadata, while `.current.json` and generation manifests belong under `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:19-28,41-45] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-34] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-109] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:6-15,134-147]\n6. Path ownership should transfer as an explicit library seam, but styles should improve on the reference's remaining positional derivation. Runtime exposes a canonical artifact-root import seam and exports its database directory from the database owner; styles currently derives corpus, manifest, and database locations independently from each module's parent directory. A single styles path module should export the styles root, corpus root, committed manifest paths, and database root, while callable APIs retain explicit path overrides for fixtures and external callers. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:3-19] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:143-155] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:31-36,80-94] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-32] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:41-45]\n7. A centralized `tests/` boundary transfers structurally: runtime separates unit, integration, lifecycle, helpers, and fixtures and owns discovery through a root config. For styles, engine tests, database tests, oracle data, and mode-adapter integration tests should be classified under one test root, but golden oracle files remain test evidence rather than corpus data or runtime database artifacts. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/vitest.config.ts:1-25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/:scoped-inventory] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:89-124] [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:20-21]\n8. The runtime should not be copied as a literal npm-package template. It has a scoped `vitest.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, and `package-lock.json`, but the expected `runtime/package.json` was absent during this pass; the styles tree likewise has no local package metadata. The safe transfer is therefore ownership and verification boundaries, not an unsupported claim that styles should immediately become an independently installable package. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/vitest.config.ts:1-25] [INFERENCE: direct read of `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/package.json` returned file-not-found, and scoped glob found no package metadata under `styles/`]\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Ruled out a literal mirror of runtime directory names: styles requires an authoritative corpus and committed corpus manifests that runtime does not own.\n- Ruled out placing `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` under `database/`: their authority and default-backend lifecycle differ from mutable SQLite publication pointers.\n- Ruled out separate top-level `engine/` and `database-code/` source domains: current bidirectional imports make one `lib/` boundary the more accurate ownership model.\n- Ruled out treating the runtime as proof that styles needs a standalone npm package: the reference package metadata is incomplete in the checked-in tree.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Copying `runtime/` mechanically is exhausted as a design direction; only its ownership rules are transferable.\n- Parent-directory derivation should not be preserved as a compatibility strategy because the restructure intentionally breaks the positional relationship it assumes.\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- Ambiguous input: \"aligned to runtime\" could mean literal topology or ownership semantics; this iteration selected ownership semantics because the prompt explicitly requires styles-specific differences.\n- Contradictory evidence: the runtime config describes a standalone `npm test` path, but no `runtime/package.json` was present. This limits package-boundary transfer but does not invalidate the observed directory/test ownership pattern.\n- Missing dependencies: `runtime/package.json` was absent; `package-lock.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `vitest.config.ts`, runtime documentation, and actual test layout were used as bounded fallback evidence.\n- Partial success: none; the transfer/difference question is answered, while exact target names and migration ordering were intentionally deferred.\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44,107-146,191-229`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-30`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:143-155`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:3-19`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/vitest.config.ts:1-25`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/` scoped inventory\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:1-36,73-109`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-34`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:9-18,52-56`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:1-147`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-32`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-32`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:645-663`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:19-28,41-45`\n\n## Assessment\n\n- New information ratio: 0.88\n- Novelty justification: Six of eight transfer-rule findings are fully new and two refine iteration 1's preliminary runtime comparison and engine/database coupling.\n- Questions addressed: Which runtime ownership boundaries transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n- Questions answered: Which runtime ownership boundaries transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n- Confidence: High for code/data/database/manifest ownership; medium-high for package-boundary conclusions because the expected runtime package manifest is absent.\n- Status: complete\n\n## Reflection\n\n- What worked and why: Comparing lifecycle and authority for each artifact class produced clearer transfer rules than matching directory names.\n- What did not work and why: Probing `runtime/package.json` failed because the file is absent, preventing a claim that the reference is a complete standalone npm package.\n- What I would do differently: The next pass should convert these ownership rules into one concrete kebab-case target tree and test each proposed location against all known path consumers.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nDerive the concrete target tree from these rules, including exact homes for corpus bundles, committed corpus manifests, sibling `lib/engine` and `lib/database` domains, thin scripts, mutable database generations, centralized tests/fixtures/oracles, and documentation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":78,"totalLines":78,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-002.md","time":{"start":1784617015083,"end":1784617015092}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_099182280ffe19e4016a5f1836f4ac8191a76d1a16beefb005"}},"id":"prt_f837697250013waInrm1FcvidP","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f83767612001jB3wO11nDnllql"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784617015110,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_3QOeGYB9LoL7X27MdSzOXOJO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"node \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\" --loop-type research --artifact-dir \".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast\" --iteration 2","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research"},"output":"OK iteration 2 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\n","metadata":{"output":"OK iteration 2 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"node \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\" --loop-type research --artifact-dir \".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast\" --iteration 2","time":{"start":1784617015103,"end":1784617015105}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_099182280ffe19e4016a5f1836f4988191b13f60e3406d15a8"}},"id":"prt_f837696ca001p1D1FC8JX9DG1q","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f83767612001jB3wO11nDnllql"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784617015577,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"id":"prt_f83769916001iR3slZy5ujaHnP","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0","messageID":"msg_f83767612001jB3wO11nDnllql","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":288225,"input":13008,"output":224,"reasoning":49,"cache":{"write":0,"read":274944}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784617019164,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"id":"prt_f8376a7160014kRym64MNV0yph","messageID":"msg_f83769ad0001ynrqPNTxqrzWEv","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","snapshot":"d35e8e585ed54efc33a6965547b7c8172b5215b0","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784617051187,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_QU2auW83DvenGQ98YIxCzYHQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] Which parts of the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` architecture transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n - [ ] What target folder layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation while remaining kebab-case?\n@@\n - [x] What is the exact current ownership and dependency topology? The corpus root mixes 1,290 bundle directories with three code/support trees and two manifests; four mode adapters and the generator are production path consumers; tests additionally bind module paths, manifests, and fixture roots; `_engine` and `_db` have bidirectional dependencies. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-29]\n+- [x] Which runtime boundaries transfer? Use one importable `lib/` with sibling engine/database domains, thin executable `scripts/`, mutable runtime artifacts under `database/`, and centralized tests. Styles intentionally adds a first-class authoritative corpus and committed corpus-manifest boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:14-23]\n@@\n - Exact path/import searches plus focused reads separated executable migration blockers from documentation-only references. (iteration 1)\n+- Classifying each artifact by authority and lifecycle produced transferable rules without mechanically copying the reference tree. (iteration 2)\n@@\n - Broad repository path searches were dominated by historical specs and generated research, so they are unsuitable as the implementation checklist without scope filtering. (iteration 1)\n+- The runtime lacks a checked-in `package.json`, so it does not support concluding that styles should become a standalone npm package. (iteration 2)\n@@\n ### Independent subtree moves -- BLOCKED (iteration 1)\n - `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` cannot be treated as unrelated rename units because manifests are root-bound and engine/database imports are bidirectional.\n+\n+### Literal runtime-tree copy -- BLOCKED (iteration 2)\n+- Runtime ownership semantics transfer, but styles also owns authoritative corpus data and committed manifests absent from the runtime.\n@@\n - Commands and agents as direct path blockers: scoped exact searches found no current matches. (iteration 1)\n+- Putting crawl/retrieval manifests under runtime `database/`: they are committed corpus metadata, not mutable SQLite publication state. (iteration 2)\n+- Separate top-level engine and database source trees: sibling domains under one `lib/` better represent their actual coupling. (iteration 2)\n@@\n - Which path constants must become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations? (iteration 1)\n+- Should golden oracle files live under centralized `tests/oracle/` while production oracle code remains under `lib/database/oracle/`? (iteration 2)\n+- What exact names should distinguish committed corpus metadata from mutable database generation manifests? (iteration 2)\n@@\n-Compare the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` ownership boundaries with the mapped styles topology, identifying what transfers directly and what must intentionally differ for authoritative corpus data, committed manifests, and opt-in runtime databases.\n+Derive the concrete kebab-case target tree, including exact homes for corpus bundles, committed corpus manifests, sibling `lib/engine` and `lib/database` domains, thin scripts, mutable database generations, centralized tests/fixtures/oracles, and documentation.\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@\n-    \"Which runtime ownership boundaries transfer directly?\",\n     \"What is the concrete kebab-case target layout?\",\n@@\n     \"Current ownership and dependency topology across data, engine, database, harness, manifests, tests, docs, and consumers\"\n+    ,\"Runtime ownership boundaries that transfer directly versus styles-specific differences\"\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"runtime-comparison-boundary\",\"summary\":\"Runtime topology transfers structurally, but styles needs first-class corpus and manifest ownership.\",\"iteration\":1}\n+    {\"id\":\"runtime-comparison-boundary\",\"summary\":\"Runtime topology transfers structurally, but styles needs first-class corpus and manifest ownership.\",\"iteration\":1},\n+    {\"id\":\"transfer-lib-scripts\",\"summary\":\"Use one importable lib boundary with sibling engine/database domains and thin executable scripts.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"intentional-corpus-boundary\",\"summary\":\"The authoritative bundle corpus and committed corpus manifests need a first-class boundary outside runtime database state.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"database-lifecycle-boundary\",\"summary\":\"The database directory should own only mutable SQLite generations, publication pointers, rollback state, locks, and sidecars.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"explicit-path-seam\",\"summary\":\"One exported path seam should replace parent-directory derivations while preserving explicit test overrides.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"centralized-tests\",\"summary\":\"Centralize engine/database/integration tests and fixtures; keep golden oracle data as test evidence.\",\"iteration\":2}\n@@\n     {\"approach\":\"Treat commands and agents as direct consumers\",\"reason\":\"Scoped exact searches found no current path matches.\",\"iteration\":1}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Literal runtime directory copy\",\"reason\":\"Styles additionally owns authoritative corpus data and committed corpus manifests.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Place corpus manifests under database runtime state\",\"reason\":\"Their authority and committed lifecycle differ from mutable publication pointers.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Separate top-level engine and database source domains\",\"reason\":\"One lib boundary with sibling domains matches current coupling.\",\"iteration\":2}\n@@\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 7,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.11,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":12,\"repository-docs\":4,\"runtime-reference\":1}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 12,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.22,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":20,\"repository-docs\":7,\"runtime-reference\":7}\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n | 1 | Current topology and path consumers | 0.89 | 9 | complete |\n+| 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n@@\n-1/5 answered. Current topology is mapped; reference transfer rules, target layout, migration order, and exact rename plan remain.\n+2/5 answered. Current topology and architecture transfer rules are resolved; target layout, migration order, and exact rename plan remain.\n@@\n-`0.89` - high first-pass novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n+`0.89 -> 0.88` - sustained high novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n@@\n - Commands/agents as current direct path consumers.\n+- Literal runtime-tree copy.\n+- Corpus manifests under mutable database state.\n+- Separate top-level engine and database code roots.\n@@\n-Compare runtime ownership boundaries and classify direct transfers versus styles-specific differences.\n+Derive and pressure-test one concrete kebab-case target tree.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -4,9 +4,8 @@\n Restructure the sk-design styles tree so 1,290 downloaded style-data folders are separated from backend code, with a concrete runtime-aligned layout, migration path, and `git mv` plan.\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] Which parts of the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` architecture transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n - [ ] What target folder layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation while remaining kebab-case?\n - [ ] What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior and avoids a flag day across imports, path constants, fixtures, commands, and docs?\n - [ ] What exact `git mv` sequence, verification ladder, rollback boundary, and compatibility policy should implementation use?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n@@ -24,32 +23,40 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n - [x] What is the exact current ownership and dependency topology? The corpus root mixes 1,290 bundle directories with three code/support trees and two manifests; four mode adapters and the generator are production path consumers; tests additionally bind module paths, manifests, and fixture roots; `_engine` and `_db` have bidirectional dependencies. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-29]\n+- [x] Which runtime boundaries transfer? Use one importable `lib/` with sibling engine/database domains, thin executable `scripts/`, mutable runtime artifacts under `database/`, and centralized tests. Styles intentionally adds a first-class authoritative corpus and committed corpus-manifest boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:14-23]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n - Exact path/import searches plus focused reads separated executable migration blockers from documentation-only references. (iteration 1)\n+- Classifying each artifact by authority and lifecycle produced transferable rules without mechanically copying the reference tree. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n - Broad repository path searches were dominated by historical specs and generated research, so they are unsuitable as the implementation checklist without scope filtering. (iteration 1)\n+- The runtime lacks a checked-in `package.json`, so it does not support concluding that styles should become a standalone npm package. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n ### Independent subtree moves -- BLOCKED (iteration 1)\n - `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` cannot be treated as unrelated rename units because manifests are root-bound and engine/database imports are bidirectional.\n+\n+### Literal runtime-tree copy -- BLOCKED (iteration 2)\n+- Runtime ownership semantics transfer, but styles also owns authoritative corpus data and committed manifests absent from the runtime.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n - Independent `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` moves without a shared path plan: internal imports and root-derived constants would break. (iteration 1)\n - Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies: update executable consumers first, documentation second. (iteration 1)\n - Commands and agents as direct path blockers: scoped exact searches found no current matches. (iteration 1)\n+- Putting crawl/retrieval manifests under runtime `database/`: they are committed corpus metadata, not mutable SQLite publication state. (iteration 2)\n+- Separate top-level engine and database source trees: sibling domains under one `lib/` better represent their actual coupling. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n@@ -65,13 +72,15 @@\n ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n - How should committed crawl/retrieval manifests be divided between authoritative corpus metadata and runtime publication metadata? (iteration 1)\n - Should engine and database modules become sibling domains under one `lib/` boundary to remove the artificial subtree cycle? (iteration 1)\n - Which path constants must become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations? (iteration 1)\n+- Should golden oracle files live under centralized `tests/oracle/` while production oracle code remains under `lib/database/oracle/`? (iteration 2)\n+- What exact names should distinguish committed corpus metadata from mutable database generation manifests? (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Compare the proven `system-deep-loop/runtime` ownership boundaries with the mapped styles topology, identifying what transfers directly and what must intentionally differ for authoritative corpus data, committed manifests, and opt-in runtime databases.\n+Derive the concrete kebab-case target tree, including exact homes for corpus bundles, committed corpus manifests, sibling `lib/engine` and `lib/database` domains, thin scripts, mutable database generations, centralized tests/fixtures/oracles, and documentation.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,27 +1,35 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"Which runtime ownership boundaries transfer directly?\",\n     \"What is the concrete kebab-case target layout?\",\n     \"What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior?\",\n     \"What exact git mv and verification plan should implementation use?\"\n   ],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     \"Current ownership and dependency topology across data, engine, database, harness, manifests, tests, docs, and consumers\"\n+    ,\"Runtime ownership boundaries that transfer directly versus styles-specific differences\"\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"topology-root-mix\",\"summary\":\"The styles root mixes 1,290 data directories with backend/support trees and two manifests.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"id\":\"manifest-root-binding\",\"summary\":\"Harness and engine constants bind both manifests and corpus discovery to the current root.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"id\":\"production-consumers\",\"summary\":\"Four design modes import the engine facade; the generator constructs engine and manifest paths positionally.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"id\":\"test-consumers\",\"summary\":\"Tests additionally bind engine fixtures, module paths, and both manifest names.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"id\":\"engine-db-cycle\",\"summary\":\"Engine and database code/tests are bidirectionally coupled and must migrate as one library boundary.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"id\":\"database-artifact-mix\",\"summary\":\"The default SQLite artifact is colocated with source/tests while persistent mode remains opt-in.\",\"iteration\":1},\n-    {\"id\":\"runtime-comparison-boundary\",\"summary\":\"Runtime topology transfers structurally, but styles needs first-class corpus and manifest ownership.\",\"iteration\":1}\n+    {\"id\":\"runtime-comparison-boundary\",\"summary\":\"Runtime topology transfers structurally, but styles needs first-class corpus and manifest ownership.\",\"iteration\":1},\n+    {\"id\":\"transfer-lib-scripts\",\"summary\":\"Use one importable lib boundary with sibling engine/database domains and thin executable scripts.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"intentional-corpus-boundary\",\"summary\":\"The authoritative bundle corpus and committed corpus manifests need a first-class boundary outside runtime database state.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"database-lifecycle-boundary\",\"summary\":\"The database directory should own only mutable SQLite generations, publication pointers, rollback state, locks, and sidecars.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"explicit-path-seam\",\"summary\":\"One exported path seam should replace parent-directory derivations while preserving explicit test overrides.\",\"iteration\":2},\n+    {\"id\":\"centralized-tests\",\"summary\":\"Centralize engine/database/integration tests and fixtures; keep golden oracle data as test evidence.\",\"iteration\":2}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\"approach\":\"Independent engine/database/harness moves\",\"reason\":\"Bidirectional imports and root-bound manifest constants make them interdependent.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"approach\":\"Treat documentation as executable migration blockers\",\"reason\":\"Docs are a secondary replacement surface after runtime path migration.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"approach\":\"Treat commands and agents as direct consumers\",\"reason\":\"Scoped exact searches found no current path matches.\",\"iteration\":1}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Literal runtime directory copy\",\"reason\":\"Styles additionally owns authoritative corpus data and committed corpus manifests.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Place corpus manifests under database runtime state\",\"reason\":\"Their authority and committed lifecycle differ from mutable publication pointers.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Separate top-level engine and database source domains\",\"reason\":\"One lib boundary with sibling domains matches current coupling.\",\"iteration\":2}\n   ],\n   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n@@ -33,12 +41,12 @@\n     \"overrides\": [],\n     \"saturatedDirections\": []\n   },\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 7,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.11,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":12,\"repository-docs\":4,\"runtime-reference\":1}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 12,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.22,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":20,\"repository-docs\":7,\"runtime-reference\":7}\n   }\n }\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -4,26 +4,30 @@\n \n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n |---|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Current topology and path consumers | 0.89 | 9 | complete |\n+| 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n \n-1/5 answered. Current topology is mapped; reference transfer rules, target layout, migration order, and exact rename plan remain.\n+2/5 answered. Current topology and architecture transfer rules are resolved; target layout, migration order, and exact rename plan remain.\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n \n-`0.89` - high first-pass novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n+`0.89 -> 0.88` - sustained high novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Independent moves of `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` without one path plan.\n - Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies.\n - Commands/agents as current direct path consumers.\n+- Literal runtime-tree copy.\n+- Corpus manifests under mutable database state.\n+- Separate top-level engine and database code roots.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Compare runtime ownership boundaries and classify direct transfers versus styles-specific differences.\n+Derive and pressure-test one concrete kebab-case target tree.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - Detached-lineage safety requires shared spec writeback, parent-resolving reducer calls, memory save, and git staging to remain deferred.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n================================================