{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784617334711,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_pFt9uUs0QZeBhOJZ8gnr0Zb8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"env -i HOME=\"$HOME\" PATH=\"$PATH\" LANG=\"$LANG\" TMPDIR=\"$TMPDIR\" USER=\"$USER\" LOGNAME=\"$LOGNAME\" OPENAI_API_KEY=\"${OPENAI_API_KEY:-}\" AI_SESSION_CHILD=1 MK_SPEC_GATE_ENFORCE=0 opencode run --model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir \"$PWD\" \"$(<'.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-003.md')\" </dev/null","timeout":900000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /Users/michelkerkmeester/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_f83780ada001IhD1a7ViiT5r3w\n\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784617175745,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f83790abf001Lz76wxWFIC1FNs\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"1f43e9aac918d49790022958fa933dd1f114ef8a\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f8378bf8a001N99Xgf5dvY5HZZ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":95822,\"input\":14556,\"output\":344,\"reasoning\":538,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":80384}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784617179131,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f837917f8001SEzxCOkdXIA416\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83790c640015IkF2VDShVghtQ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"snapshot\":\"1f43e9aac918d49790022958fa933dd1f114ef8a\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784617183858,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_kNnAwukZUJbpZudjuesqUVyl\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"date -u +\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research\"},\"output\":\"2026-07-21T06:59:43Z\\n\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"2026-07-21T06:59:43Z\\n\",\"exit\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"date -u +\\\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\\\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784617183853,\"end\":1784617183856}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_01fffe67e12e13e5016a5f18dee6fc8191b63d96f1d1d6ccba\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f837926da001UK0tQzbDaAjl4K\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83790c640015IkF2VDShVghtQ\"}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1784617184364,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f83792c6900114NCDHlTn4Svo7\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"1f43e9aac918d49790022958fa933dd1f114ef8a\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83790c640015IkF2VDShVghtQ\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":104995,\"input\":10027,\"output\":72,\"reasoning\":176,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":94720}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1784617187892,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f83793a32001MoBTUysDXntdXx\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83792f050015RvdI6yUDdjxX8\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"snapshot\":\"1f43e9aac918d49790022958fa933dd1f114ef8a\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1784617208534,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f83798358001yGth9p0RYBXkGW\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f83792f050015RvdI6yUDdjxX8\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The pressure test resolves the remaining naming fork: use `library/` for committed corpus data, `lib/` for reusable code, `scripts/` for thin entrypoints, `database/` only for mutable projection state, and `tests/oracle/` for all oracle machinery because repository imports show it is test-only. I’ll record the exact tree and class-by-class map now; the only naming exceptions are conventional `README.md` and immutable bundle-internal artifact contracts such as `DESIGN.md`, not newly introduced structural names.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1784617206616,\"end\":1784617208532},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0216802cc7fe7058016a5f18f69590819189bf440690edc6f8\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1784617327886,\"sessionID\":\"ses_07c8850fbffehqa1FW6u0wgXSS\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"apply_patch\",\"callID\":\"call_Sy78mktXFBKQqW2zjPCdWUA5\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"error\",\"input\":{\"patchText\":\"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-003.md\\n+# Iteration 3: Concrete Target Tree and Artifact Ownership\\n+\\n+## Focus\\n+\\n+Derive and pressure-test one concrete kebab-case target tree, assigning every current artifact class an exact owner. This iteration resolves names and ownership only; dependency ordering and exact `git mv` commands remain the next iteration.\\n+\\n+## Actions Taken\\n+\\n+1. Inventoried every file under `_engine/`, `_db/`, and `_harness/` and classified it as reusable source, executable entrypoint, mutable state, test support, test evidence, or documentation.\\n+2. Traced path defaults and direct-execution code in the style facade, database operator, schema, generation manifest, indexer, and extractor.\\n+3. Traced every oracle import to determine whether any oracle module is used by production code.\\n+4. Pressure-tested structural names against kebab-case, lifecycle ownership, the flat-bundle authority contract, and the `legacy|shadow|persistent` mode contract.\\n+\\n+## Findings\\n+\\n+1. The concrete target should use six ownership boundaries under `styles/`: committed `library/`, reusable `lib/`, executable `scripts/`, mutable `database/`, test-only `tests/`, and explanatory `docs/`. This is the smallest layout that separates all requested lifecycles without recreating `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` as cosmetic top-level renames. The root README remains the entry document. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles:directory-listing] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44] [INFERENCE: iteration-002.md findings 1-5 establish the lifecycle boundaries]\\n+\\n+2. The authoritative corpus should be `library/bundles/<style-slug>/`, while committed metadata should be `library/manifests/crawl-manifest.json` and `library/manifests/retrieval-manifest.json`. The `bundles/` layer is not artificial: it prevents the indexer from mistaking a metadata directory for a bundle and gives the 1,290 homogeneous bundle units one enumerable root. The two manifest names describe authority rather than mutability: crawl provenance versus deterministic retrieval index. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:648-662] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-32,589-645] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:19-28,41-45]\\n+\\n+3. One exported ownership seam, `lib/paths.mjs`, should own `stylesRoot`, `bundleRoot`, `crawlManifestPath`, `retrievalManifestPath`, `databaseRoot`, and `defaultDatabasePath`. Production defaults should import these exports; callable APIs should retain explicit `corpusRoot`, `manifestPath`, and `databasePath` overrides so fixture isolation remains intact. This replaces three incompatible parent-directory derivations without a compatibility shim. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:34-36,80-94,123-127,169-173] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-16,31-32] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:41-45]\\n+\\n+4. `_engine` source maps one-for-one to `lib/engine/`, including `style-library.mjs`; `_db` production source maps to sibling `lib/database/`. `style-library.mjs` and `operator.mjs` currently combine reusable exports with direct process dispatch, so each should first move into `lib/` and then lose its CLI tail to a new thin script (`scripts/style-library.mjs` and `scripts/style-database.mjs`). Moving either combined file directly into `scripts/` would violate the reusable-source boundary. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:80-220,248-260] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs:75-213] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:9-18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/retrieval.mjs:5-7]\\n+\\n+5. All current oracle modules are test apparatus, not production database code: scoped imports originate only from `_db/__tests__` or other oracle modules. Therefore `differential-oracle.mjs`, `query-set.mjs`, `replay-fixtures.mjs`, `relevance-judgments.mjs`, the judgment seed, and `golden/` all belong under `tests/oracle/`; there is no evidence-backed `lib/database/oracle/` class. Golden JSON and the relevance seed are committed test evidence, while the `.mjs` files are executable test support. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs:11-30] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/fixtures.test.mjs:10-19] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/judgments.test.mjs:19-25] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/differential-oracle.mjs:5-23,105-138] [INFERENCE: scoped oracle import search returned no production importer]\\n+\\n+6. Test ownership centralizes without flattening domains: engine tests go to `tests/engine/`, database tests to `tests/database/`, the engine corpus builder becomes `tests/fixtures/corpus.mjs`, and database-specific fixtures remain `tests/database/fixtures.mjs`. Mode-adapter tests outside `styles/` remain with their owning modes and update imports only; moving them would transfer ownership rather than merely restructure styles. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/:scoped-inventory] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/:scoped-inventory] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/__tests__/relationship-blueprint.test.mjs:16-23] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/comparison-lane.test.mjs:16-23]\\n+\\n+7. Mutable `database/` owns generated SQLite files, content-addressed generations, `.current.json` publication manifests, rollback candidates, locks, and `-wal`/`-shm` sidecars only. No source, committed corpus manifest, or oracle evidence belongs there. The current default colocates `style-library.sqlite` beside `schema.mjs`; moving the default through `lib/paths.mjs` separates publication state while preserving opt-in persistent behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-22] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-10,22-34] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs:58-73,123-154]\\n+\\n+8. Structural names introduced by the migration are kebab-case. Conventional `README.md` and immutable downloaded bundle artifacts such as `DESIGN.md` are explicit contract exceptions, not new structural names: renaming bundle internals would mutate authoritative corpus content and invalidate manifests rather than merely restructure directories. Existing style directory slugs and golden filenames already use kebab-case. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:5-8] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:694-792] [INFERENCE: preserving flat bundle bytes is required by the authoritative-corpus contract and the research non-goal]\\n+\\n+## Concrete Target Tree\\n+\\n+```text\\n+.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/\\n+|-- README.md\\n+|-- library/\\n+|   |-- bundles/\\n+|   |   `-- <1,290-style-slug>/\\n+|   |       |-- DESIGN.md\\n+|   |       |-- css-variables.css\\n+|   |       |-- design-tokens.json\\n+|   |       |-- source.md\\n+|   |       |-- tailwind-v4.css\\n+|   |       `-- <style-slug>-canonical.json\\n+|   `-- manifests/\\n+|       |-- crawl-manifest.json\\n+|       `-- retrieval-manifest.json\\n+|-- lib/\\n+|   |-- paths.mjs\\n+|   |-- engine/\\n+|   |   |-- cards.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- corpus-use-proof.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- eligibility.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- hydrate.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- manifest.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- ordering.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- persistent-adapter.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- rank-fts.mjs\\n+|   |   `-- style-library.mjs\\n+|   `-- database/\\n+|       |-- canonical.mjs\\n+|       |-- generation-manifest.mjs\\n+|       |-- indexer.mjs\\n+|       |-- operator.mjs\\n+|       |-- retrieval.mjs\\n+|       |-- schema.mjs\\n+|       |-- stage-telemetry.mjs\\n+|       `-- vectors.mjs\\n+|-- scripts/\\n+|   |-- extract-refero.mjs\\n+|   |-- style-database.mjs\\n+|   `-- style-library.mjs\\n+|-- database/\\n+|   `-- <mutable sqlite generations, publication pointers, locks, sidecars>\\n+|-- tests/\\n+|   |-- engine/\\n+|   |   |-- check-stable.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- eligibility-first.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- fallback.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- hydrate-guard.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- index.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- invalidation.test.mjs\\n+|   |   `-- proof.test.mjs\\n+|   |-- database/\\n+|   |   |-- adapter.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- fixtures.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- fixtures.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- index.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- indexer.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- judgments.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- manifest.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- operator.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- oracle.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- retrieval.test.mjs\\n+|   |   |-- schema.test.mjs\\n+|   |   `-- telemetry.test.mjs\\n+|   |-- fixtures/\\n+|   |   `-- corpus.mjs\\n+|   `-- oracle/\\n+|       |-- differential-oracle.mjs\\n+|       |-- query-set.mjs\\n+|       |-- relevance-judgments.mjs\\n+|       |-- relevance-judgments.seed.json\\n+|       |-- replay-fixtures.mjs\\n+|       `-- golden/\\n+|           |-- index.json\\n+|           |-- scales.json\\n+|           `-- *.canonical.json\\n+`-- docs/\\n+    |-- acquisition.md\\n+    |-- database.md\\n+    `-- manual-testing-playbook.md\\n+```\\n+\\n+## Exact Current-to-Target Ownership Map\\n+\\n+| Current artifact class | Exact destination | Rule |\\n+|---|---|---|\\n+| 1,290 root style directories | `library/bundles/<style-slug>/` | Move as authoritative six-artifact bundle units; do not rename contents. |\\n+| `_manifest.json` | `library/manifests/crawl-manifest.json` | Committed acquisition/provenance metadata. |\\n+| `_retrieval-manifest.json` | `library/manifests/retrieval-manifest.json` | Committed deterministic legacy retrieval index. |\\n+| `_engine/{cards,corpus-use-proof,eligibility,hydrate,manifest,ordering,persistent-adapter,rank-fts}.mjs` | `lib/engine/<same-name>.mjs` | Reusable engine source. |\\n+| `_engine/style-library.mjs` | `lib/engine/style-library.mjs` | Reusable facade; direct-execution block moves to a new thin script. |\\n+| `_db/{canonical,generation-manifest,indexer,retrieval,schema,stage-telemetry,vectors}.mjs` | `lib/database/<same-name>.mjs` | Reusable persistent-projection source. |\\n+| `_db/operator.mjs` | `lib/database/operator.mjs` | Reusable lifecycle API; direct-execution block moves to a new thin script. |\\n+| `_harness/extract-refero.mjs` | `scripts/extract-refero.mjs` | Acquisition executable; imports shared paths. |\\n+| New style-library CLI adapter | `scripts/style-library.mjs` | Thin process adapter calling `lib/engine/style-library.mjs`. |\\n+| New database CLI adapter | `scripts/style-database.mjs` | Thin process adapter calling `lib/database/operator.mjs`. |\\n+| `_engine/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `_engine/__tests__/index.mjs` | `tests/engine/` | Engine test cases and test index. |\\n+| `_engine/__tests__/fixtures.mjs` | `tests/fixtures/corpus.mjs` | Shared corpus fixture API used across engine, database, oracle, and mode tests. |\\n+| `_db/__tests__/*.test.mjs`, `_db/__tests__/index.mjs` | `tests/database/` | Database test cases and test index. |\\n+| `_db/__tests__/fixtures.mjs` | `tests/database/fixtures.mjs` | Database-specific fixture API. |\\n+| `_db/oracle/*.mjs` | `tests/oracle/<same-name>.mjs` | Test-only oracle support; no production importer exists. |\\n+| `_db/oracle/relevance-judgments.seed.json` | `tests/oracle/relevance-judgments.seed.json` | Committed oracle evidence. |\\n+| `_db/oracle/golden/*` | `tests/oracle/golden/*` | Committed golden evidence. |\\n+| `_db/README.md` | `docs/database.md` | Persistent projection lifecycle documentation. |\\n+| `_harness/README.md` | `docs/acquisition.md` | Corpus acquisition documentation. |\\n+| Root `manual-testing-playbook.md` | `docs/manual-testing-playbook.md` | Styles-local manual test documentation. |\\n+| Root `README.md` | `README.md` | Root navigation and ownership overview. |\\n+| Current/generated `style-library.sqlite*` family | `database/style-library.sqlite*` | Mutable, ignored publication state; relocate/rebuild, never treat as committed source. |\\n+| External mode adapters and tests | Stay with owning mode; update imports and fixture paths | Consumers, not styles-owned artifacts. |\\n+\\n+## Ruled Out\\n+\\n+- Ruled out `corpus/` as the top-level data name: `library/` distinguishes committed product data from source `lib/` and matches the requested ownership vocabulary more directly.\\n+- Ruled out putting manifests directly beside 1,290 bundle folders: the current indexer enumerates directories, so a `manifests/` sibling would require special-case filtering and preserve a mixed enumeration root.\\n+- Ruled out `lib/database/oracle/`: every checked importer is test code, so calling these modules production source would misstate ownership.\\n+- Ruled out moving `style-library.mjs` or `operator.mjs` directly to `scripts/`: both expose reusable APIs consumed by tests and other modules.\\n+- Ruled out retaining old path shims by default: checked-in consumers can migrate atomically, while explicit API path overrides already provide fixture/external flexibility.\\n+\\n+## Dead Ends\\n+\\n+- A literal all-files-kebab-case rule cannot include conventional `README.md` or downloaded `DESIGN.md` without changing established documentation and corpus artifact contracts. Apply kebab-case to all structural names introduced or moved by this restructure and record those two contract exceptions explicitly.\\n+- Splitting oracle code between `lib/database/oracle/` and `tests/oracle/` has no evidence-based boundary in the current repository; the entire current oracle subtree is test-owned.\\n+\\n+## Edge Cases\\n+\\n+- Ambiguous input: “flat bundles authoritative” means flat files within each bundle, not that all 1,290 bundle directories must remain direct children of `styles/`; `library/bundles/` preserves bundle contents and authority while separating ownership domains.\\n+- Contradictory evidence: prior strategy phrased some oracle code as potentially production-owned, but import evidence shows no production consumer. This iteration resolves the contradiction in favor of `tests/oracle/`.\\n+- Missing dependencies: no resource map exists, so repository imports and inventories remain authoritative.\\n+- Partial success: the target tree and ownership question are answered; dependency ordering and exact `git mv` sequencing are intentionally deferred.\\n+\\n+## Sources Consulted\\n+\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/` scoped inventory\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/` scoped inventory\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/` scoped inventory\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:1-261`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs:1-240`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:1-32`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:1-80`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:645-663`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/differential-oracle.mjs:1-167`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/replay-fixtures.mjs:1-180`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/relevance-judgments.mjs:1-130`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/query-set.mjs:1-43`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs:1-100`\\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/extract-refero.mjs:1-90`\\n+- Scoped exact-path and oracle-import searches under `.opencode/skills/sk-design/`\\n+\\n+## Assessment\\n+\\n+- New information ratio: 0.84\\n+- Novelty justification: Six of eight findings are fully new target-layout decisions, while two refine prior ownership rules with exact names and evidence-backed exceptions.\\n+- Questions addressed: What target layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation?\\n+- Questions answered: What target layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation?\\n+- Confidence: High for current artifact ownership and target boundaries; medium-high for final filenames because implementation may expose an unrecorded external path consumer, which iteration 4 must test before fixing compatibility policy.\\n+- Status: complete\\n+\\n+## Reflection\\n+\\n+- What worked and why: Combining complete subtree inventories with import-direction evidence prevented source/test misclassification and gave every present artifact one owner.\\n+- What did not work and why: Treating “production oracle code” as an assumed category failed the import test; current oracle code is wholly test-owned.\\n+- What I would do differently: The next pass should convert this map into dependency-ordered move groups, with path-seam introduction preceding physical moves and executable/import verification after each group.\\n+\\n+## Recommended Next Focus\\n+\\n+Derive the dependency-ordered migration and exact `git mv` sequence for this tree, including the path-seam cut, temporary mixed-state boundaries, consumer updates, verification ladder, rollback point, and evidence-based decision on whether any compatibility shim is required.\\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":3,\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration state_source=externalized_files do_not_switch_mode=true\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.84,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Six of eight findings are fully new target-layout decisions, while two refine prior ownership rules with exact names and evidence-backed exceptions.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Concrete kebab-case target tree and exact ownership of every current artifact class.\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":8,\\\"keyQuestions\\\":[\\\"What target layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation?\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"What target layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation?\\\"],\\\"ruledOut\\\":[\\\"Top-level corpus name instead of library\\\",\\\"Manifests beside bundle directories\\\",\\\"Production lib/database/oracle subtree\\\",\\\"Moving combined facades directly into scripts\\\",\\\"Default old-path compatibility shims\\\",\\\"Renaming immutable bundle artifact contracts\\\"],\\\"focusTrack\\\":\\\"architecture\\\",\\\"edgeCase\\\":\\\"contradictory-evidence\\\",\\\"toolsUsed\\\":[\\\"Read\\\",\\\"Glob\\\",\\\"Grep\\\",\\\"Bash\\\"],\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\\\",\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\"deep-research-strategy.md\\\",\\\"findings-registry.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-dashboard.md\\\",\\\"iterations/iteration-001.md\\\",\\\"iterations/iteration-002.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_harness/\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-07-21T06:59:43Z\\\",\\\"durationMs\\\":654000,\\\"graphEvents\\\":[],\\\"executor\\\":{\\\"kind\\\":\\\"cli-opencode\\\",\\\"model\\\":\\\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\\\",\\\"reasoningEffort\\\":null,\\\"serviceTier\\\":null}}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"target-six-boundaries\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"The target uses library, lib, scripts, database, tests, and docs as lifecycle ownership boundaries.\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"library-bundles-manifests\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Authoritative bundles belong under library/bundles and committed crawl/retrieval metadata under library/manifests.\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"single-path-seam\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"lib/paths.mjs is the one exported owner of corpus, manifest, and mutable database defaults while APIs retain explicit overrides.\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"facade-cli-split\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"Combined facade/operator files move to lib first and gain new thin scripts rather than moving wholesale into scripts.\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"oracle-test-owned\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"All current oracle code and evidence is test-owned; no production importer supports lib/database/oracle.\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"finding\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"database-state-only\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"database owns only mutable SQLite generations, pointers, rollback state, locks, and sidecars.\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"ruled-out\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Production lib/database/oracle subtree\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"Scoped imports show all current oracle modules are consumed only by tests or other oracle modules.\\\",\\\"evidence\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs:11-30\\\"}\\n+{\\\"type\\\":\\\"ruled-out\\\",\\\"run\\\":3,\\\"approach\\\":\\\"Manifests beside bundle directories\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"A manifests directory in the bundle enumeration root would need a special-case exclusion and preserve mixed ownership.\\\",\\\"evidence\\\":\\\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:648-662\\\"}\\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\\n@@\\n {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":2,\\\"run\\\":2,\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"target_agent\\\":\\\"deep-research\\\",\\\"agent_definition_loaded\\\":true,\\\"resolved_route\\\":\\\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration state_source=externalized_files do_not_switch_mode=true\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.88,\\\"noveltyJustification\\\":\\\"Six of eight transfer-rule findings are fully new and two refine iteration 1's preliminary runtime comparison and engine/database coupling.\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"Reference-architecture transfer rules and i