{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784617618095,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_O3FLWiUfULx3G9ASuKGlEUh7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] What target folder layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation while remaining kebab-case?\n - [ ] What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior and avoids a flag day across imports, path constants, fixtures, commands, and docs?\n@@\n - [x] Which runtime boundaries transfer? Use one importable `lib/` with sibling engine/database domains, thin executable `scripts/`, mutable runtime artifacts under `database/`, and centralized tests. Styles intentionally adds a first-class authoritative corpus and committed corpus-manifest boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:14-23]\n+- [x] What is the target layout? Use `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts`, mutable `database`, centralized `tests`, and `docs`, with `lib/paths.mjs` as the sole default-path seam. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:14-97]\n@@\n - Classifying each artifact by authority and lifecycle produced transferable rules without mechanically copying the reference tree. (iteration 2)\n+- Mapping every current artifact class into a shallow ownership tree resolved the concrete names and preserved legacy/default/persistent semantics. (iteration 3)\n@@\n - The runtime lacks a checked-in `package.json`, so it does not support concluding that styles should become a standalone npm package. (iteration 2)\n+- The first iteration-3 dispatch attempted one combined append patch and failed atomically; the retry succeeded by creating artifacts independently and appending state without matching prior JSONL. (iteration 3)\n@@\n - Separate top-level engine and database source trees: sibling domains under one `lib/` better represent their actual coupling. (iteration 2)\n+- A top-level `manifests/` shared by committed corpus metadata and mutable publication state: it would merge lifecycles again. (iteration 3)\n+- Wrapper roots such as `backend/`, `runtime/`, or `src/`: `styles/` is already the subsystem root and each direct child has a concrete owner. (iteration 3)\n+- Filesystem compatibility aliases for `_engine`, `_db`, `_harness`, or root manifests absent a concrete external consumer. (iteration 3)\n@@\n - What exact names should distinguish committed corpus metadata from mutable database generation manifests? (iteration 2)\n+- Resolve the iteration-2/3 oracle-ownership contradiction by proving whether oracle `.mjs` modules have any production importer. (iteration 3)\n+- Which moved modules must preserve names one-for-one, rather than introducing unimplemented adapter splits? (iteration 3)\n@@\n-Derive the concrete kebab-case target tree, including exact homes for corpus bundles, committed corpus manifests, sibling `lib/engine` and `lib/database` domains, thin scripts, mutable database generations, centralized tests/fixtures/oracles, and documentation.\n+Derive the dependency-ordered implementation and exact shell-safe `git mv` sequence, including import/path cutover, baseline and post-move verification, mutable-database handling, one-commit rollback boundary, and the no-filesystem-shim compatibility policy.\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@\n-    \"What is the concrete kebab-case target layout?\",\n     \"What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior?\",\n@@\n     ,\"Runtime ownership boundaries that transfer directly versus styles-specific differences\"\n+    ,\"Concrete kebab-case target layout and artifact ownership map\"\n@@\n     {\"id\":\"centralized-tests\",\"summary\":\"Centralize engine/database/integration tests and fixtures; keep golden oracle data as test evidence.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"concrete-target-tree\",\"summary\":\"Use direct library, lib, scripts, database, tests, and docs roots under styles, without backend/runtime/src wrappers.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"committed-manifest-names\",\"summary\":\"Use library/manifests/crawl-manifest.json and retrieval-manifest.json; mutable generation metadata remains database-owned.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"single-path-seam\",\"summary\":\"lib/paths.mjs owns defaults while callable APIs retain explicit fixture and external overrides.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"semantic-contract-preservation\",\"summary\":\"The target preserves authoritative bundles, legacy default, and opt-in persistent projection behavior.\",\"iteration\":3}\n@@\n     ,{\"approach\":\"Separate top-level engine and database source domains\",\"reason\":\"One lib boundary with sibling domains matches current coupling.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Top-level manifests shared across lifecycles\",\"reason\":\"Committed corpus metadata and mutable database publication state require separate owners.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Backend/runtime/src wrapper root\",\"reason\":\"No additional ownership distinction justifies another nesting layer.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Filesystem compatibility aliases\",\"reason\":\"No concrete external or persisted-path consumer currently requires them.\",\"iteration\":3}\n@@\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 12,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.22,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":20,\"repository-docs\":7,\"runtime-reference\":7}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 16,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.33,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":22,\"repository-docs\":10,\"runtime-reference\":8,\"prior-iteration-evidence\":2}\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n | 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n+| 3 | Concrete target tree and ownership map | 0.88 | 8 | complete after one retry |\n@@\n-2/5 answered. Current topology and architecture transfer rules are resolved; target layout, migration order, and exact rename plan remain.\n+3/5 answered. Topology, transfer rules, and target layout are resolved; migration order and exact rename/verification plan remain.\n@@\n-`0.89 -> 0.88` - sustained high novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n+`0.89 -> 0.88 -> 0.88` - sustained high novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n@@\n - Separate top-level engine and database code roots.\n+- Shared top-level manifests root.\n+- Extra backend/runtime/src wrapper roots.\n+- Old-path filesystem aliases without a concrete external consumer.\n@@\n-Derive and pressure-test one concrete kebab-case target tree.\n+Produce the dependency-ordered migration and exact shell-safe `git mv` plan.\n@@\n - Detached-lineage safety requires shared spec writeback, parent-resolving reducer calls, memory save, and git staging to remain deferred.\n+- Oracle ownership is contradictory across iterations 2 and 3 and needs an exact-import adjudication before synthesis.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -4,9 +4,8 @@\n Restructure the sk-design styles tree so 1,290 downloaded style-data folders are separated from backend code, with a concrete runtime-aligned layout, migration path, and `git mv` plan.\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n-- [ ] What target folder layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation while remaining kebab-case?\n - [ ] What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior and avoids a flag day across imports, path constants, fixtures, commands, and docs?\n - [ ] What exact `git mv` sequence, verification ladder, rollback boundary, and compatibility policy should implementation use?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n@@ -24,21 +23,24 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n - [x] What is the exact current ownership and dependency topology? The corpus root mixes 1,290 bundle directories with three code/support trees and two manifests; four mode adapters and the generator are production path consumers; tests additionally bind module paths, manifests, and fixture roots; `_engine` and `_db` have bidirectional dependencies. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-29]\n - [x] Which runtime boundaries transfer? Use one importable `lib/` with sibling engine/database domains, thin executable `scripts/`, mutable runtime artifacts under `database/`, and centralized tests. Styles intentionally adds a first-class authoritative corpus and committed corpus-manifest boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:14-23]\n+- [x] What is the target layout? Use `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts`, mutable `database`, centralized `tests`, and `docs`, with `lib/paths.mjs` as the sole default-path seam. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:14-97]\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n - Exact path/import searches plus focused reads separated executable migration blockers from documentation-only references. (iteration 1)\n - Classifying each artifact by authority and lifecycle produced transferable rules without mechanically copying the reference tree. (iteration 2)\n+- Mapping every current artifact class into a shallow ownership tree resolved the concrete names and preserved legacy/default/persistent semantics. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n - Broad repository path searches were dominated by historical specs and generated research, so they are unsuitable as the implementation checklist without scope filtering. (iteration 1)\n - The runtime lacks a checked-in `package.json`, so it does not support concluding that styles should become a standalone npm package. (iteration 2)\n+- The first iteration-3 dispatch attempted one combined append patch and failed atomically; the retry succeeded by creating artifacts independently and appending state without matching prior JSONL. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n@@ -55,8 +57,11 @@\n - Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies: update executable consumers first, documentation second. (iteration 1)\n - Commands and agents as direct path blockers: scoped exact searches found no current matches. (iteration 1)\n - Putting crawl/retrieval manifests under runtime `database/`: they are committed corpus metadata, not mutable SQLite publication state. (iteration 2)\n - Separate top-level engine and database source trees: sibling domains under one `lib/` better represent their actual coupling. (iteration 2)\n+- A top-level `manifests/` shared by committed corpus metadata and mutable publication state: it would merge lifecycles again. (iteration 3)\n+- Wrapper roots such as `backend/`, `runtime/`, or `src/`: `styles/` is already the subsystem root and each direct child has a concrete owner. (iteration 3)\n+- Filesystem compatibility aliases for `_engine`, `_db`, `_harness`, or root manifests absent a concrete external consumer. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n@@ -74,13 +79,15 @@\n - Should engine and database modules become sibling domains under one `lib/` boundary to remove the artificial subtree cycle? (iteration 1)\n - Which path constants must become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations? (iteration 1)\n - Should golden oracle files live under centralized `tests/oracle/` while production oracle code remains under `lib/database/oracle/`? (iteration 2)\n - What exact names should distinguish committed corpus metadata from mutable database generation manifests? (iteration 2)\n+- Resolve the iteration-2/3 oracle-ownership contradiction by proving whether oracle `.mjs` modules have any production importer. (iteration 3)\n+- Which moved modules must preserve names one-for-one, rather than introducing unimplemented adapter splits? (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Derive the concrete kebab-case target tree, including exact homes for corpus bundles, committed corpus manifests, sibling `lib/engine` and `lib/database` domains, thin scripts, mutable database generations, centralized tests/fixtures/oracles, and documentation.\n+Derive the dependency-ordered implementation and exact shell-safe `git mv` sequence, including import/path cutover, baseline and post-move verification, mutable-database handling, one-commit rollback boundary, and the no-filesystem-shim compatibility policy.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,13 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    \"What is the concrete kebab-case target layout?\",\n     \"What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior?\",\n     \"What exact git mv and verification plan should implementation use?\"\n   ],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     \"Current ownership and dependency topology across data, engine, database, harness, manifests, tests, docs, and consumers\"\n     ,\"Runtime ownership boundaries that transfer directly versus styles-specific differences\"\n+    ,\"Concrete kebab-case target layout and artifact ownership map\"\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"topology-root-mix\",\"summary\":\"The styles root mixes 1,290 data directories with backend/support trees and two manifests.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"id\":\"manifest-root-binding\",\"summary\":\"Harness and engine constants bind both manifests and corpus discovery to the current root.\",\"iteration\":1},\n@@ -20,16 +20,23 @@\n     {\"id\":\"intentional-corpus-boundary\",\"summary\":\"The authoritative bundle corpus and committed corpus manifests need a first-class boundary outside runtime database state.\",\"iteration\":2},\n     {\"id\":\"database-lifecycle-boundary\",\"summary\":\"The database directory should own only mutable SQLite generations, publication pointers, rollback state, locks, and sidecars.\",\"iteration\":2},\n     {\"id\":\"explicit-path-seam\",\"summary\":\"One exported path seam should replace parent-directory derivations while preserving explicit test overrides.\",\"iteration\":2},\n     {\"id\":\"centralized-tests\",\"summary\":\"Centralize engine/database/integration tests and fixtures; keep golden oracle data as test evidence.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"concrete-target-tree\",\"summary\":\"Use direct library, lib, scripts, database, tests, and docs roots under styles, without backend/runtime/src wrappers.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"committed-manifest-names\",\"summary\":\"Use library/manifests/crawl-manifest.json and retrieval-manifest.json; mutable generation metadata remains database-owned.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"single-path-seam\",\"summary\":\"lib/paths.mjs owns defaults while callable APIs retain explicit fixture and external overrides.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"id\":\"semantic-contract-preservation\",\"summary\":\"The target preserves authoritative bundles, legacy default, and opt-in persistent projection behavior.\",\"iteration\":3}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\"approach\":\"Independent engine/database/harness moves\",\"reason\":\"Bidirectional imports and root-bound manifest constants make them interdependent.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"approach\":\"Treat documentation as executable migration blockers\",\"reason\":\"Docs are a secondary replacement surface after runtime path migration.\",\"iteration\":1},\n     {\"approach\":\"Treat commands and agents as direct consumers\",\"reason\":\"Scoped exact searches found no current path matches.\",\"iteration\":1}\n     ,{\"approach\":\"Literal runtime directory copy\",\"reason\":\"Styles additionally owns authoritative corpus data and committed corpus manifests.\",\"iteration\":2}\n     ,{\"approach\":\"Place corpus manifests under database runtime state\",\"reason\":\"Their authority and committed lifecycle differ from mutable publication pointers.\",\"iteration\":2}\n     ,{\"approach\":\"Separate top-level engine and database source domains\",\"reason\":\"One lib boundary with sibling domains matches current coupling.\",\"iteration\":2}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Top-level manifests shared across lifecycles\",\"reason\":\"Committed corpus metadata and mutable database publication state require separate owners.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Backend/runtime/src wrapper root\",\"reason\":\"No additional ownership distinction justifies another nesting layer.\",\"iteration\":3}\n+    ,{\"approach\":\"Filesystem compatibility aliases\",\"reason\":\"No concrete external or persisted-path consumer currently requires them.\",\"iteration\":3}\n   ],\n   \"observedIdeas\": [],\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n@@ -41,12 +48,12 @@\n     \"overrides\": [],\n     \"saturatedDirections\": []\n   },\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 12,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.22,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":20,\"repository-docs\":7,\"runtime-reference\":7}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 16,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.33,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"repository-code\":22,\"repository-docs\":10,\"runtime-reference\":8,\"prior-iteration-evidence\":2}\n   }\n }\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -5,16 +5,17 @@\n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n |---|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Current topology and path consumers | 0.89 | 9 | complete |\n | 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n+| 3 | Concrete target tree and ownership map | 0.88 | 8 | complete after one retry |\n \n ## Question Status\n \n-2/5 answered. Current topology and architecture transfer rules are resolved; target layout, migration order, and exact rename plan remain.\n+3/5 answered. Topology, transfer rules, and target layout are resolved; migration order and exact rename/verification plan remain.\n \n ## Convergence Trend\n \n-`0.89 -> 0.88` - sustained high novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n+`0.89 -> 0.88 -> 0.88` - sustained high novelty; convergence is telemetry only until iteration 5.\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Independent moves of `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` without one path plan.\n@@ -22,12 +23,16 @@\n - Commands/agents as current direct path consumers.\n - Literal runtime-tree copy.\n - Corpus manifests under mutable database state.\n - Separate top-level engine and database code roots.\n+- Shared top-level manifests root.\n+- Extra backend/runtime/src wrapper roots.\n+- Old-path filesystem aliases without a concrete external consumer.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Derive and pressure-test one concrete kebab-case target tree.\n+Produce the dependency-ordered migration and exact shell-safe `git mv` plan.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - Detached-lineage safety requires shared spec writeback, parent-resolving reducer calls, memory save, and git staging to remain deferred.\n+- Oracle ownership is contradictory across iterations 2 and 3 and needs an exact-import adjudication before synthesis.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","