{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618214385,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_uv9c1qaHgx57Rl1MXlBivJyF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-005.md\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 5 of 5\n+Questions: 5/5 charter questions answered | Last focus: dependency order and exact git move plan\n+Last 2 ratios: 0.88 -> 0.86 | Stuck count: 0\n+Stop policy: max-iterations; this final audit is mandatory.\n+Next focus: Adversarially audit and adjudicate the complete plan before synthesis.\n+\n+Research Topic: Restructure the sk-design styles tree so the 1290 downloaded style data folders are separated from backend code, aligned to system-deep-loop/runtime, with kebab-case, a concrete target layout, migration path, and git-mv plan.\n+Iteration: 5 of 5\n+Focus Area: Final conformance audit, contradiction resolution, inventory completeness, command safety, and implementation-ready adjudication.\n+Remaining Key Questions: No charter questions remain; audit the answers.\n+Carried-Forward Audit Items:\n+- Audit every tracked source, test, script, documentation artifact, production consumer, and generator path against the target map.\n+- Confirm all moved source filenames remain represented and avoid invented/removal claims.\n+- Resolve target-tree drift between iteration 3 and iteration 4 (no speculative wrappers, oracle entirely test-owned).\n+- Evaluate the manifest-derived 1,290-source `git mv` argv for platform command-length and partial-failure risks; correct if needed.\n+- Confirm baseline commands and relocated test runners are real and sufficient.\n+- Confirm mutable DB ignore/default handling does not imply committing runtime artifacts.\n+Last 3 Iterations Summary: target tree 0.88; migration plan 0.86; all questions answered but final audit required.\n+Pivot Lineage: none.\n+Saturated Directions: literal runtime copy, independent subtree moves, lifecycle-mixed manifests, wrapper roots, filesystem aliases, wildcard/whole-directory moves, speculative CLI wrappers, production oracle placement, and database creation during source migration.\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Registry: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+- Prior iterations: iterations/iteration-001.md through iteration-004.md\n+- Write narrative: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-005.md\n+- Write delta: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-005.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- Act as the `deep-research` LEAF for one final iteration. State first, no sub-agents.\n+- Source tree and Git index are read-only. Only narrative, append-only state, and delta may be written.\n+- Do not execute moves, source edits, staging, memory save, reducer edits, or synthesis.\n+- Audit actual files and imports, not only prior prose. Findings must distinguish confirmed corrections from retained recommendations.\n+- Produce a final adjudicated target tree and migration verdict, naming any iteration-3/4 recommendation that must be superseded.\n+- The exact move plan must be shell-safe on macOS, deterministic, scoped, and rollback-aware. Prefer the smallest command mechanism that is robust to 1,290 names and special characters.\n+- Verify all 17 production source modules (or actual count), 37 database-tree files, 17 engine-tree files, 2 harness files, two manifests, 1,290 bundle roots, direct consumers, and documentation/test surfaces as actual inventory permits.\n+- Every recommendation needs file citations or explicit grounded inference.\n+\n+## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n+\n+Produce exactly three artifacts. Canonical state/delta record must include iteration/run 5, route proof, novelty, status/focus/count, questions/adjudications, ruled-out directions, tools/sources, timestamp/duration, optional graphEvents, and executor provenance for `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`. Create narrative/delta independently and append state without matching prior long JSONL lines. Do not edit config, strategy, registry, dashboard, or research.md.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-005.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-005.md\n================================================================