{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618831410,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kAYptVjBK0zS0pdFND3CqRAj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard\n2: \n3: ## Iterations\n4: \n5: | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n6: |---|---|---:|---:|---|\n7: | 1 | Current topology and path consumers | 0.89 | 9 | complete |\n8: | 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n9: | 3 | Concrete target tree and ownership map | 0.88 | 8 | complete after one retry |\n10: | 4 | Dependency order and exact git move plan | 0.86 | 8 | complete |\n11: \n12: ## Question Status\n13: \n14: 5/5 charter questions answered. Iteration 5 is a mandatory audit/adjudication pass under `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n15: \n16: ## Convergence Trend\n17: \n18: `0.89 -> 0.88 -> 0.88 -> 0.86` - sustained novelty; convergence remains telemetry until iteration 5.\n19: \n20: ## Dead Ends\n21: \n22: - Independent moves of `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` without one path plan.\n23: - Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies.\n24: - Commands/agents as current direct path consumers.\n25: - Literal runtime-tree copy.\n26: - Corpus manifests under mutable database state.\n27: - Separate top-level engine and database code roots.\n28: - Shared top-level manifests root.\n29: - Extra backend/runtime/src wrapper roots.\n30: - Old-path filesystem aliases without a concrete external consumer.\n31: - Wildcard/whole-directory move commands.\n32: - Speculative CLI wrappers and production oracle placement.\n33: - Moving or creating mutable database state during source migration.\n34: \n35: ## Next Focus\n36: \n37: Audit and adjudicate the complete target tree and migration plan before synthesis.\n38: \n39: ## Active Risks\n40: \n41: - Detached-lineage safety requires shared spec writeback, parent-resolving reducer calls, memory save, and git staging to remain deferred.\n42: - Oracle ownership contradiction is resolved by exact imports in iteration 4: all current oracle consumers are tests.\n43: - Audit the 1,290-source move for command-length and partial-failure behavior before finalizing.\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iterations\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Current topology and path consumers | 0.89 | 9 | complete |\n| 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n| 3 | Concrete target tree and ownership map | 0.88 | 8 | complete after one retry |\n| 4 | Dependency order and exact git move plan | 0.86 | 8 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n5/5 charter questions answered. Iteration 5 is a mandatory audit/adjudication pass under `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n`0.89 -> 0.88 -> 0.88 -> 0.86` - sustained novelty; convergence remains telemetry until iteration 5.\n\n## Dead Ends","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard\n\n## Iterations\n\n| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---|\n| 1 | Current topology and path consumers | 0.89 | 9 | complete |\n| 2 | Runtime transfer rules and differences | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n| 3 | Concrete target tree and ownership map | 0.88 | 8 | complete after one retry |\n| 4 | Dependency order and exact git move plan | 0.86 | 8 | complete |\n\n## Question Status\n\n5/5 charter questions answered. Iteration 5 is a mandatory audit/adjudication pass under `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n\n## Convergence Trend\n\n`0.89 -> 0.88 -> 0.88 -> 0.86` - sustained novelty; convergence remains telemetry until iteration 5.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Independent moves of `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` without one path plan.\n- Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies.\n- Commands/agents as current direct path consumers.\n- Literal runtime-tree copy.\n- Corpus manifests under mutable database state.\n- Separate top-level engine and database code roots.\n- Shared top-level manifests root.\n- Extra backend/runtime/src wrapper roots.\n- Old-path filesystem aliases without a concrete external consumer.\n- Wildcard/whole-directory move commands.\n- Speculative CLI wrappers and production oracle placement.\n- Moving or creating mutable database state during source migration.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nAudit and adjudicate the complete target tree and migration plan before synthesis.\n\n## Active Risks\n\n- Detached-lineage safety requires shared spec writeback, parent-resolving reducer calls, memory save, and git staging to remain deferred.\n- Oracle ownership contradiction is resolved by exact imports in iteration 4: all current oracle consumers are tests.\n- Audit the 1,290-source move for command-length and partial-failure behavior before finalizing.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":43,"totalLines":43,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784618831397,"end":1784618831404}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_068cbeef00a37f50016a5f1f4f2a4881918016377193936a92"}},"id":"prt_f83924e22001uAlZjOIGJDKgHA","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f8391f0990012QX85dO4kleVbS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618831410,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Hg4zvnzc3K8i2FjNTzTnR1YB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: sk-design Styles Tree Restructure\n2: \n3: ## 2. TOPIC\n4: Restructure the sk-design styles tree so 1,290 downloaded style-data folders are separated from backend code, with a concrete runtime-aligned layout, migration path, and `git mv` plan.\n5: \n6: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n7: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n8: [All five charter questions are evidence-backed; iteration 5 performs mandatory adversarial audit and final adjudication.]\n9: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n10: \n11: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n12: - Do not move or modify the 1,290 data folders during research.\n13: - Do not decide whether persistent SQLite becomes the default retrieval mode; preserve the current `legacy|shadow|persistent` contract.\n14: - Do not redesign retrieval algorithms or database schemas.\n15: - Do not add compatibility shims unless a concrete external or persisted-path consumer requires them.\n16: \n17: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n18: - Complete exactly five evidence iterations; convergence before iteration five is telemetry only.\n19: - Produce a concrete target tree, dependency-ordered migration, and explicit `git mv` plan.\n20: - Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption or a write-boundary violation.\n21: \n22: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n23: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n24: - [x] What is the exact current ownership and dependency topology? The corpus root mixes 1,290 bundle directories with three code/support trees and two manifests; four mode adapters and the generator are production path consumers; tests additionally bind module paths, manifests, and fixture roots; `_engine` and `_db` have bidirectional dependencies. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-29]\n25: - [x] Which runtime boundaries transfer? Use one importable `lib/` with sibling engine/database domains, thin executable `scripts/`, mutable runtime artifacts under `database/`, and centralized tests. Styles intentionally adds a first-class authoritative corpus and committed corpus-manifest boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:14-23]\n26: - [x] What is the target layout? Use `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts`, mutable `database`, centralized `tests`, and `docs`, with `lib/paths.mjs` as the sole default-path seam. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:14-97]\n27: - [x] What migration preserves behavior? Introduce explicit paths against old defaults, move coupled code/tests while old data remains, then move manifest-enumerated bundles/manifests and flip defaults, then update mutable-state rules/docs. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:7-32]\n28: - [x] What exact move/verification/rollback policy should implementation use? Use tracked, explicit source lists plus a validated manifest-derived bundle argv; no old-path aliases, no mutable DB move, group gates after each runnable mixed state, and one revertable migration commit. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:34-179]\n29: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n30: \n31: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n32: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n33: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n34: - Exact path/import searches plus focused reads separated executable migration blockers from documentation-only references. (iteration 1)\n35: - Classifying each artifact by authority and lifecycle produced transferable rules without mechanically copying the reference tree. (iteration 2)\n36: - Mapping every current artifact class into a shallow ownership tree resolved the concrete names and preserved legacy/default/persistent semantics. (iteration 3)\n37: - Exact tracked-file and manifest inventories converted the target tree into a shell-safe, dependency-ordered migration with runnable mixed states. (iteration 4)\n38: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n39: \n40: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n41: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n42: - Broad repository path searches were dominated by historical specs and generated research, so they are unsuitable as the implementation checklist without scope filtering. (iteration 1)\n43: - The runtime lacks a checked-in `package.json`, so it does not support concluding that styles should become a standalone npm package. (iteration 2)\n44: - The first iteration-3 dispatch attempted one combined append patch and failed atomically; the retry succeeded by creating artifacts independently and appending state without matching prior JSONL. (iteration 3)\n45: - Whole-directory and wildcard moves fail safety requirements because `_db` may contain ignored mutable artifacts and root wildcards can capture backend/docs. (iteration 4)\n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n47: \n48: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n49: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n50: ### Independent subtree moves -- BLOCKED (iteration 1)\n51: - `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` cannot be treated as unrelated rename units because manifests are root-bound and engine/database imports are bidirectional.\n52: \n53: ### Literal runtime-tree copy -- BLOCKED (iteration 2)\n54: - Runtime ownership semantics transfer, but styles also owns authoritative corpus data and committed manifests absent from the runtime.\n55: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n56: \n57: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n58: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n59: - Independent `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` moves without a shared path plan: internal imports and root-derived constants would break. (iteration 1)\n60: - Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies: update executable consumers first, documentation second. (iteration 1)\n61: - Commands and agents as direct path blockers: scoped exact searches found no current matches. (iteration 1)\n62: - Putting crawl/retrieval manifests under runtime `database/`: they are committed corpus metadata, not mutable SQLite publication state. (iteration 2)\n63: - Separate top-level engine and database source trees: sibling domains under one `lib/` better represent their actual coupling. (iteration 2)\n64: - A top-level `manifests/` shared by committed corpus metadata and mutable publication state: it would merge lifecycles again. (iteration 3)\n65: - Wrapper roots such as `backend/`, `runtime/`, or `src/`: `styles/` is already the subsystem root and each direct child has a concrete owner. (iteration 3)\n66: - Filesystem compatibility aliases for `_engine`, `_db`, `_harness`, or root manifests absent a concrete external consumer. (iteration 3)\n67: - Speculative CLI wrappers: preserve dual-purpose module contracts one-for-one until a separate need justifies extraction. (iteration 4)\n68: - Production oracle placement: exact imports prove the current oracle subtree is entirely test-owned. (iteration 4)\n69: - Moving or creating SQLite state during source migration: persistent state is rebuildable, opt-in, and a separate operational concern. (iteration 4)\n70: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n71: \n72: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n73: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n74: - Completed pivots: 0\n75: - Failed pivots: 0\n76: - Audited overrides: 0\n77: - Saturated: none yet\n78: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n79: - Remaining frontier: current topology, reference architecture, target layout, migration ordering, and rename verification\n80: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n83: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n84: - How should committed crawl/retrieval manifests be divided between authoritative corpus metadata and runtime publication metadata? (iteration 1)\n85: - Should engine and database modules become sibling domains under one `lib/` boundary to remove the artificial subtree cycle? (iteration 1)\n86: - Which path constants must become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations? (iteration 1)\n87: - Should golden oracle files live under centralized `tests/oracle/` while production oracle code remains under `lib/database/oracle/`? (iteration 2)\n88: - What exact names should distinguish committed corpus metadata from mutable database generation manifests? (iteration 2)\n89: - Resolve the iteration-2/3 oracle-ownership contradiction by proving whether oracle `.mjs` modules have any production importer. (iteration 3)\n90: - Which moved modules must preserve names one-for-one, rather than introducing unimplemented adapter splits? (iteration 3)\n91: - Audit the 1,290-source argv against platform command-length and partial-failure risks; prefer the simplest deterministic safe form. (iteration 4)\n92: - Audit every tracked source, consumer, ignore rule, and test entrypoint against the proposed G0-G5 plan. (iteration 4)\n93: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n94: \n95: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n96: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n97: Adversarially audit the complete target tree and migration plan against tracked inventory, imports, ignored mutable state, command length/partial failure, test coverage, and naming; resolve contradictions and deliver the final adjudicated recommendation.\n98: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n99: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n100: \n101: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n102: - The confirmed gap analysis reports 1,290 downloaded directories mixed with `_db`, `_engine`, `_harness`, and two root manifests. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-42]\n103: - The current corpus README calls `_engine/style-library.mjs` the committed retrieval surface and keeps extraction state in `_harness` plus `_manifest.json`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:3-18]\n104: - Persistent retrieval remains opt-in; `legacy` is the default and flat files remain authoritative. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:134-147]\n105: - The proven runtime separates domain code under `lib/`, executable adapters under `scripts/`, and real SQLite files under `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-25]\n106: - `resource-map.md` was absent at initialization; skipping the coverage-map preload.\n107: - Focused memory retrieval returned no canonical packet results, so repository files are the authority for this lineage.\n108: \n109: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n110: - Source pointers: `styles/README.md`, `styles/_engine/**`, `styles/_db/**`, `styles/_harness/**`, `sk-design/SKILL.md`, four design-mode corpus consumers, and `system-deep-loop/runtime/**`.\n111: - Reuse candidates: runtime `lib/`, `database/`, `scripts/`, `tests/`, and README ownership boundaries.\n112: - Integration points: import specifiers, manifest constants, database defaults, fixture roots, CLI examples, feature catalog, manual test playbooks, and the design generator's study preparation.\n113: - Constraints: research-only; all writes stay inside this detached lineage directory; shared spec writeback, reducer calls resolving the parent packet, memory save, and git staging are deferred.\n114: \n115: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n116: - Max iterations: 5\n117: - Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before the hard cap\n118: - Stop policy: max-iterations\n119: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n120: - Progressive synthesis: false\n121: - Current generation: 1\n122: - Started: 2026-07-21T06:43:40Z\n\n(End of file - total 122 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: sk-design Styles Tree Restructure\n\n## 2. TOPIC\nRestructure the sk-design styles tree so 1,290 downloaded style-data folders are separated from backend code, with a concrete runtime-aligned layout, migration path, and `git mv` plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n[All five charter questions are evidence-backed; iteration 5 performs mandatory adversarial audit and final adjudication.]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Do not move or modify the 1,290 data folders during research.\n- Do not decide whether persistent SQLite becomes the default retrieval mode; preserve the current `legacy|shadow|persistent` contract.\n- Do not redesign retrieval algorithms or database schemas.\n- Do not add compatibility shims unless a concrete external or persisted-path consumer requires them.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n- Complete exactly five evidence iterations; convergence before iteration five is telemetry only.\n- Produce a concrete target tree, dependency-ordered migration, and explicit `git mv` plan.\n- Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption or a write-boundary violation.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: sk-design Styles Tree Restructure\n\n## 2. TOPIC\nRestructure the sk-design styles tree so 1,290 downloaded style-data folders are separated from backend code, with a concrete runtime-aligned layout, migration path, and `git mv` plan.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n[All five charter questions are evidence-backed; iteration 5 performs mandatory adversarial audit and final adjudication.]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Do not move or modify the 1,290 data folders during research.\n- Do not decide whether persistent SQLite becomes the default retrieval mode; preserve the current `legacy|shadow|persistent` contract.\n- Do not redesign retrieval algorithms or database schemas.\n- Do not add compatibility shims unless a concrete external or persisted-path consumer requires them.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n- Complete exactly five evidence iterations; convergence before iteration five is telemetry only.\n- Produce a concrete target tree, dependency-ordered migration, and explicit `git mv` plan.\n- Stop early only for unrecoverable state corruption or a write-boundary violation.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- [x] What is the exact current ownership and dependency topology? The corpus root mixes 1,290 bundle directories with three code/support trees and two manifests; four mode adapters and the generator are production path consumers; tests additionally bind module paths, manifests, and fixture roots; `_engine` and `_db` have bidirectional dependencies. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-001.md:14-29]\n- [x] Which runtime boundaries transfer? Use one importable `lib/` with sibling engine/database domains, thin executable `scripts/`, mutable runtime artifacts under `database/`, and centralized tests. Styles intentionally adds a first-class authoritative corpus and committed corpus-manifest boundary. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-002.md:14-23]\n- [x] What is the target layout? Use `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts`, mutable `database`, centralized `tests`, and `docs`, with `lib/paths.mjs` as the sole default-path seam. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-003.md:14-97]\n- [x] What migration preserves behavior? Introduce explicit paths against old defaults, move coupled code/tests while old data remains, then move manifest-enumerated bundles/manifests and flip defaults, then update mutable-state rules/docs. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:7-32]\n- [x] What exact move/verification/rollback policy should implementation use? Use tracked, explicit source lists plus a validated manifest-derived bundle argv; no old-path aliases, no mutable DB move, group gates after each runnable mixed state, and one revertable migration commit. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:34-179]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- Exact path/import searches plus focused reads separated executable migration blockers from documentation-only references. (iteration 1)\n- Classifying each artifact by authority and lifecycle produced transferable rules without mechanically copying the reference tree. (iteration 2)\n- Mapping every current artifact class into a shallow ownership tree resolved the concrete names and preserved legacy/default/persistent semantics. (iteration 3)\n- Exact tracked-file and manifest inventories converted the target tree into a shell-safe, dependency-ordered migration with runnable mixed states. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- Broad repository path searches were dominated by historical specs and generated research, so they are unsuitable as the implementation checklist without scope filtering. (iteration 1)\n- The runtime lacks a checked-in `package.json`, so it does not support concluding that styles should become a standalone npm package. (iteration 2)\n- The first iteration-3 dispatch attempted one combined append patch and failed atomically; the retry succeeded by creating artifacts independently and appending state without matching prior JSONL. (iteration 3)\n- Whole-directory and wildcard moves fail safety requirements because `_db` may contain ignored mutable artifacts and root wildcards can capture backend/docs. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n### Independent subtree moves -- BLOCKED (iteration 1)\n- `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` cannot be treated as unrelated rename units because manifests are root-bound and engine/database imports are bidirectional.\n\n### Literal runtime-tree copy -- BLOCKED (iteration 2)\n- Runtime ownership semantics transfer, but styles also owns authoritative corpus data and committed manifests absent from the runtime.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Independent `_engine`, `_db`, and `_harness` moves without a shared path plan: internal imports and root-derived constants would break. (iteration 1)\n- Treating documentation references as runtime dependencies: update executable consumers first, documentation second. (iteration 1)\n- Commands and agents as direct path blockers: scoped exact searches found no current matches. (iteration 1)\n- Putting crawl/retrieval manifests under runtime `database/`: they are committed corpus metadata, not mutable SQLite publication state. (iteration 2)\n- Separate top-level engine and database source trees: sibling domains under one `lib/` better represent their actual coupling. (iteration 2)\n- A top-level `manifests/` shared by committed corpus metadata and mutable publication state: it would merge lifecycles again. (iteration 3)\n- Wrapper roots such as `backend/`, `runtime/`, or `src/`: `styles/` is already the subsystem root and each direct child has a concrete owner. (iteration 3)\n- Filesystem compatibility aliases for `_engine`, `_db`, `_harness`, or root manifests absent a concrete external consumer. (iteration 3)\n- Speculative CLI wrappers: preserve dual-purpose module contracts one-for-one until a separate need justifies extraction. (iteration 4)\n- Production oracle placement: exact imports prove the current oracle subtree is entirely test-owned. (iteration 4)\n- Moving or creating SQLite state during source migration: persistent state is rebuildable, opt-in, and a separate operational concern. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: current topology, reference architecture, target layout, migration ordering, and rename verification\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n- How should committed crawl/retrieval manifests be divided between authoritative corpus metadata and runtime publication metadata? (iteration 1)\n- Should engine and database modules become sibling domains under one `lib/` boundary to remove the artificial subtree cycle? (iteration 1)\n- Which path constants must become explicit ownership exports rather than parent-directory derivations? (iteration 1)\n- Should golden oracle files live under centralized `tests/oracle/` while production oracle code remains under `lib/database/oracle/`? (iteration 2)\n- What exact names should distinguish committed corpus metadata from mutable database generation manifests? (iteration 2)\n- Resolve the iteration-2/3 oracle-ownership contradiction by proving whether oracle `.mjs` modules have any production importer. (iteration 3)\n- Which moved modules must preserve names one-for-one, rather than introducing unimplemented adapter splits? (iteration 3)\n- Audit the 1,290-source argv against platform command-length and partial-failure risks; prefer the simplest deterministic safe form. (iteration 4)\n- Audit every tracked source, consumer, ignore rule, and test entrypoint against the proposed G0-G5 plan. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nAdversarially audit the complete target tree and migration plan against tracked inventory, imports, ignored mutable state, command length/partial failure, test coverage, and naming; resolve contradictions and deliver the final adjudicated recommendation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- The confirmed gap analysis reports 1,290 downloaded directories mixed with `_db`, `_engine`, `_harness`, and two root manifests. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-42]\n- The current corpus README calls `_engine/style-library.mjs` the committed retrieval surface and keeps extraction state in `_harness` plus `_manifest.json`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:3-18]\n- Persistent retrieval remains opt-in; `legacy` is the default and flat files remain authoritative. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:134-147]\n- The proven runtime separates domain code under `lib/`, executable adapters under `scripts/`, and real SQLite files under `database/`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/README.md:23-44] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/README.md:10-25]\n- `resource-map.md` was absent at initialization; skipping the coverage-map preload.\n- Focused memory retrieval returned no canonical packet results, so repository files are the authority for this lineage.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Source pointers: `styles/README.md`, `styles/_engine/**`, `styles/_db/**`, `styles/_harness/**`, `sk-design/SKILL.md`, four design-mode corpus consumers, and `system-deep-loop/runtime/**`.\n- Reuse candidates: runtime `lib/`, `database/`, `scripts/`, `tests/`, and README ownership boundaries.\n- Integration points: import specifiers, manifest constants, database defaults, fixture roots, CLI examples, feature catalog, manual test playbooks, and the design generator's study preparation.\n- Constraints: research-only; all writes stay inside this detached lineage directory; shared spec writeback, reducer calls resolving the parent packet, memory save, and git staging are deferred.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before the hard cap\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: false\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-21T06:43:40Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":122,"totalLines":122,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784618831393,"end":1784618831407}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_068cbeef00a37f50016a5f1f4f2a3c81919302e151de1c7505"}},"id":"prt_f83924e1e001YVCP5DTmEY4tc7","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f8391f0990012QX85dO4kleVbS"}}
