{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618994205,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FbSJUzhyaBhGsXEzNpCOWbgw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ### Question Injection Surface\n34: \n35: Use `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n36: \n37: - `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n38: - `text`: question text to promote\n39: - `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n40: - `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n41: - `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n42: - `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n43: \n44: The reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n45: \n46: Question ownership is explicit:\n47: \n48: - Inbox rows are immutable input.\n49: - The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n50: - Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n51: \n52: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. TOPIC\n57: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n62: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n63: Generated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n64: \n65: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n66: - [ ] [Question 2]\n67: - [ ] [Question 3]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n73: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n78: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n83: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n84: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n90: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n91: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n92: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n93: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n99: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n100: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n101: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n107: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n108: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n109: \n110: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n111: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n112: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n113: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n114: \n115: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n116: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n117: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n124: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n125: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n126: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n131: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n132: - Completed pivots: 0\n133: - Failed pivots: 0\n134: - Audited overrides: 0\n135: - Saturated: none yet\n136: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n137: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n138: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n143: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n144: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n150: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n151: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n152: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n157: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n158: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n159: \n160: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n161: \n162: Populate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n163: \n164: - Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n165: - Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n166: - Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n167: - Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n168: \n169: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n174: - Max iterations: [from config]\n175: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n176: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n177: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n178: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n179: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n180: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n181: - Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n182: - Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n183: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n184: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json`\n185: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md`\n186: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n187: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n188: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n### Question Injection Surface\n\nUse `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n\n- `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n- `text`: question text to promote\n- `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n- `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n- `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n- `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n\nThe reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n\nQuestion ownership is explicit:\n\n- Inbox rows are immutable input.\n- The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n- Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\nGenerated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n\n- Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n- Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n- Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n- Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n- Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n- Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":188,"totalLines":188,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784618994195,"end":1784618994204}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a8124b415486d47016a5f1ff20c588191b4ac0385275ad5d8"}},"id":"prt_f8394ca11001O0qZtrL5eRkmNV","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f839482f500141Fmcpe2hr0dEH"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618994214,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_ivskED2VFOJPoOsm7uuVofWf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"17-section|## 17|Executive Summary|Research Synthesis|Eliminated Alternatives|Divergence Map","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 22 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/manual-testing-playbook/synthesis-save-and-guardrails/ruled-out-directions-in-synthesis.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Verify that iteration ruledOut data is consolidated into an Eliminated Alternatives section in research/research.md.\"\n\n  Line 15: This scenario validates that ruled-out directions are properly synthesized for `DR-026`. The objective is to verify that `ruledOut` data from iteration JSONL records and `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files are consolidated into a mandatory \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section in `research/research.md`.\n\n  Line 27: - Objective: Verify that iteration ruledOut data is consolidated into \"Eliminated Alternatives\" in research/research.md.\n\n  Line 32: - Expected signals: research/research.md has a mandatory \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section formatted as a table (`| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`); iteration files have `## Ruled Out` and `## Dead Ends` sections when negative knowledge is captured; strategy.md has a `## 10. Ruled Out Directions` section updated per iteration; ALWAYS rule 10 mandates documenting ruled-out directions.\n\n  Line 33: - Pass/fail posture: PASS if the synthesis phase produces an \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section in research/research.md consolidating all ruledOut and Dead Ends data, and the upstream sources (JSONL, iteration files, strategy.md) consistently feed this section; FAIL if the section is missing, data is not consolidated, or upstream sources lack the required fields.\n\n  Line 48: 1. `bash: rg -n 'Eliminated Alternatives\\|ruledOut\\|Dead Ends\\|negative knowledge' .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md`\n\n  Line 53: research/research.md has mandatory \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section as a table; iteration files have `## Ruled Out` and `## Dead Ends` sections; strategy.md has `## 10. Ruled Out Directions` section; JSONL records include `ruledOut` array; ALWAYS rule 10 mandates per-iteration documentation of ruled-out directions.\n\n  Line 55: Capture the loop protocol synthesis rules (Step 3 with Eliminated Alternatives), the state format ruledOut array schema and iteration file requirements, the strategy template Ruled Out Directions section, and SKILL.md ALWAYS rule 10.\n\n  Line 57: PASS if the synthesis phase produces an \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section in research/research.md consolidating all ruledOut and Dead Ends data, and upstream sources consistently feed this section; FAIL if the section is missing, data is not consolidated, or upstream sources lack the required fields.\n\n  Line 75: | `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md` | Loop protocol; inspect `ANCHOR:phase-synthesis` for the Eliminated Alternatives consolidation rules (synthesis Step 3) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:\n  Line 86: Synthesis owns the final `research/research.md` output. It reads all iteration files and the final strategy state, compiles the standard 17-section research document, adds the required `Eliminated Alternatives` table, marks the config status complete, and appends a `synthesis_complete` event to the JSONL log.\n\n  Line 442: Iteration files include `Ruled Out` and `Dead Ends` sections, JSONL records can carry structured `ruledOut` entries, and the reducer promotes those failed paths into the strategy and findings registry. Final synthesis then consolidates them into the required `Eliminated Alternatives` section so later iterations and later readers do not repeat dead paths.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature-catalog/research-output/progressive-synthesis.md:\n  Line 29: The final workflow still owns synthesis. After convergence, the synth phase reads all iteration files and the final strategy state, deduplicates overlap, and cleans the document into the canonical 17-section structure. If `progressiveSynthesis` is disabled, the loop skips iteration-time writes and creates `research/research.md` from scratch during synthesis, but the file remains the workflow-owned final research surface in both modes.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature-catalog/research-output/negative-knowledge.md:\n  Line 29: The reducer and synthesis phases keep that information alive. `reduce-state.cjs` promotes ruled-out directions into the strategy and findings registry so future iterations can avoid retrying blocked paths. Final synthesis then consolidates those eliminated paths into the required `Eliminated Alternatives` table inside `research/research.md`, which turns negative knowledge into a durable research output.\n\n  Line 41: | `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md` | Reference | Defines the `Eliminated Alternatives` synthesis contract. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/feature-catalog/loop-lifecycle/synthesis.md:\n  Line 27: The synthesis phase reads every iteration file plus the final strategy state, then writes the canonical `research/research.md` document in the standard 17-section format. This phase owns deduplication and final organization even when progressive synthesis has already been updating the file during earlier iterations.\n\n  Line 29: Negative knowledge is part of the live contract here. Synthesis must consolidate `ruledOut` entries and `Dead Ends` sections into a required `Eliminated Alternatives` table. It also updates the config status to `complete` and appends a `synthesis_complete` event so later tooling can tell the packet has reached terminal synthesis.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:\n  Line 670: Verify that iteration ruledOut data is consolidated into \"Eliminated Alternatives\" in research/research.md.\n\n  Line 673: Prompt summary: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the ruled-out directions synthesis contract for deep-research against the current deep-research docs, command entrypoint, YAML workflow, and runtime anchors. Verify the synthesis phase consolidates ruledOut entries from JSONL records and ## Dead Ends sections from iteration files into a mandatory \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section in research/research.md. Verify that strategy.md also tracks ruled-out directions per iteration. Return a concise operator-facing verdict.\n\n  Line 675: Expected signals: research/research.md has a mandatory \"Eliminated Alternatives\" section formatted as a table (`| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`); iteration files have `## Ruled Out` and `## Dead Ends` sections when negative knowledge is captured; strategy.md has a `## 10. Ruled Out Directions` section updated per iteration; ALWAYS rule 10 mandates documenting ruled-out directions.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md:\n  Line 535: 3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n\n  Line 542:    - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n","metadata":{"matches":22,"truncated":false},"title":"17-section|## 17|Executive Summary|Research Synthesis|Eliminated Alternatives|Divergence Map","time":{"start":1784618994198,"end":1784618994213}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a8124b415486d47016a5f1ff20c688191867eb8f75c776cde"}},"id":"prt_f8394ca14001GkVg4z9Ubhqhwf","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f839482f500141Fmcpe2hr0dEH"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618994220,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BpbELjV9fkUSMGhBoULrNYk7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-005.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-005.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":5,\"run\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration state_source=externalized_files do_not_switch_mode=true\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Three findings are new corrections (measured argv safety, missing generator gate, and absent mutable-state ignores), while four adjudications consolidate or sharpen prior inventory and ownership evidence.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final conformance audit, contradiction resolution, inventory completeness, command safety, and implementation-ready adjudication.\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"keyQuestions\":[\"Do all tracked sources, tests, consumers, manifests, bundles, documentation surfaces, and generators map to the target without omission?\",\"Which iteration-3/4 recommendations survive adversarial audit, and which must be superseded?\",\"Is the 1,290-source git move shell-safe, deterministic, argument-safe, and rollback-aware?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"All tracked artifact classes and consumers have adjudicated destinations.\",\"Iteration 4 supersedes iteration 3's wrappers and production oracle; iteration 5 corrects iteration 4's preflight, generator gate, pointer probe, ignore policy, and documentation inventory.\",\"One preflighted spawnSync git-mv argv is retained at 57,205 bytes against ARG_MAX 1,048,576.\"],\"adjudications\":[\"Retain library/lib separation and paths.mjs seam\",\"Preserve 17 production modules one-for-one\",\"Move complete oracle subtree to tests\",\"Retain one preflighted manifest-derived git mv invocation\",\"Add generator typecheck and baseline test\",\"Ignore mutable database payload except README\",\"Rewrite 1,290 README links and active path docs\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Chunked, xargs, wildcard, shell-expanded, or per-bundle git moves\",\"Whole backend subtree moves\",\"Speculative wrappers\",\"Production oracle\",\"Committed mutable database artifacts\",\"Fixture manif... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n2: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"closed-inventory-adjudicated\",\"summary\":\"Confirmed 17 production modules, 37 database-tree files, 17 engine-tree files, 2 harness files, 2 manifests, 1,290 six-file bundle roots, and 7,800 total tracked styles files; every class has a target.\"}\n3: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"single-argv-safe-with-preflight\",\"summary\":\"The argv is 57,205 bytes versus ARG_MAX 1,048,576; retain one shell-free git mv after exact bundle, empty destination, collision, and headroom checks.\"}\n4: {\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"iteration-3-tree-drift\",\"summary\":\"Supersede scripts/style-library.mjs, scripts/style-database.mjs, and lib/database/oracle.mjs; preserve dual-purpose modules and keep oracle test-owned.\"}\n5: {\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"generator-baseline-gap\",\"summary\":\"Add backend typecheck and corpus-baseline-v3 targeted test at baseline and mixed-state gates.\"}\n6: {\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"mutable-database-policy\",\"summary\":\"No sk-design ignore or mutable DB exists; ignore database/* except README and probe style-library.sqlite.current.json.\"}\n7: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"documentation-link-inventory\",\"summary\":\"Rewrite the 1,290 root-relative styles README links plus active skill, catalog, playbook, mode, generator, and packet docs.\"}\n8: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Chunked or per-source bundle moves\",\"reason\":\"The one-process argv is far below ARG_MAX and avoids additional partial-failure boundaries and ordering complexity.\"}\n\n(End of file - total 8 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":5,\"run\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration state_source=externalized_files do_not_switch_mode=true\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Three findings are new corrections (measured argv safety, missing generator gate, and absent mutable-state ignores), while four adjudications consolidate or sharpen prior inventory and ownership evidence.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final conformance audit, contradiction resolution, inventory completeness, command safety, and implementation-ready adjudication.\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"keyQuestions\":[\"Do all tracked sources, tests, consumers, manifests, bundles, documentation surfaces, and generators map to the target without omission?\",\"Which iteration-3/4 recommendations survive adversarial audit, and which must be superseded?\",\"Is the 1,290-source git move shell-safe, deterministic, argument-safe, and rollback-aware?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"All tracked artifact classes and consumers have adjudicated destinations.\",\"Iteration 4 supersedes iteration 3's wrappers and production oracle; iteration 5 corrects iteration 4's preflight, generator gate, pointer probe, ignore policy, and documentation inventory.\",\"One preflighted spawnSync git-mv argv is retained at 57,205 bytes against ARG_MAX 1,048,576.\"],\"adjudications\":[\"Retain library/lib separation and paths.mjs seam\",\"Preserve 17 production modules one-for-one\",\"Move complete oracle subtree to tests\",\"Retain one preflighted manifest-derived git mv invocation\",\"Add generator typecheck and baseline test\",\"Ignore mutable database payload except README\",\"Rewrite 1,290 README links and active path docs\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Chunked, xargs, wildcard, shell-expanded, or per-bundle git moves\",\"Whole backend subtree moves\",\"Speculative wrappers\",\"Production oracle\",\"Committed mutable database artifacts\",\"Fixture manif... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"closed-inventory-adjudicated\",\"summary\":\"Confirmed 17 production modules, 37 database-tree files, 17 engine-tree files, 2 harness files, 2 manifests, 1,290 six-file bundle roots, and 7,800 total tracked styles files; every class has a target.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"single-argv-safe-with-preflight\",\"summary\":\"The argv is 57,205 bytes versus ARG_MAX 1,048,576; retain one shell-free git mv after exact bundle, empty destination, collision, and headroom checks.\"}\n{\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"iteration-3-tree-drift\",\"summary\":\"Supersede scripts/style-library.mjs, scripts/style-database.mjs, and lib/database/oracle.mjs; preserve dual-purpose modules and keep oracle test-owned.\"}\n{\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"generator-baseline-gap\",\"summary\":\"Add backend typecheck and corpus-baseline-v3 targeted test at baseline and mixed-state gates.\"}\n{\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"mutable-database-policy\",\"summary\":\"No sk-design ignore or mutable DB exists; ignore database/* except README and probe style-library.sqlite.current.json.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"documentation-link-inventory\",\"summary\":\"Rewrite the 1,290 root-relative styles README links plus active skill, catalog, playbook, mode, generator, and packet docs.\"}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Chunked or per-source bundle moves\",\"reason\":\"The one-process argv is far below ARG_MAX and avoids additional partial-failure boundaries and ordering complexity.\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-005.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":5,\"run\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration state_source=externalized_files do_not_switch_mode=true\",\"newInfoRatio\":0.44,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Three findings are new corrections (measured argv safety, missing generator gate, and absent mutable-state ignores), while four adjudications consolidate or sharpen prior inventory and ownership evidence.\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final conformance audit, contradiction resolution, inventory completeness, command safety, and implementation-ready adjudication.\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"keyQuestions\":[\"Do all tracked sources, tests, consumers, manifests, bundles, documentation surfaces, and generators map to the target without omission?\",\"Which iteration-3/4 recommendations survive adversarial audit, and which must be superseded?\",\"Is the 1,290-source git move shell-safe, deterministic, argument-safe, and rollback-aware?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"All tracked artifact classes and consumers have adjudicated destinations.\",\"Iteration 4 supersedes iteration 3's wrappers and production oracle; iteration 5 corrects iteration 4's preflight, generator gate, pointer probe, ignore policy, and documentation inventory.\",\"One preflighted spawnSync git-mv argv is retained at 57,205 bytes against ARG_MAX 1,048,576.\"],\"adjudications\":[\"Retain library/lib separation and paths.mjs seam\",\"Preserve 17 production modules one-for-one\",\"Move complete oracle subtree to tests\",\"Retain one preflighted manifest-derived git mv invocation\",\"Add generator typecheck and baseline test\",\"Ignore mutable database payload except README\",\"Rewrite 1,290 README links and active path docs\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Chunked, xargs, wildcard, shell-expanded, or per-bundle git moves\",\"Whole backend subtree moves\",\"Speculative wrappers\",\"Production oracle\",\"Committed mutable database artifacts\",\"Fixture manif... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"closed-inventory-adjudicated\",\"summary\":\"Confirmed 17 production modules, 37 database-tree files, 17 engine-tree files, 2 harness files, 2 manifests, 1,290 six-file bundle roots, and 7,800 total tracked styles files; every class has a target.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"single-argv-safe-with-preflight\",\"summary\":\"The argv is 57,205 bytes versus ARG_MAX 1,048,576; retain one shell-free git mv after exact bundle, empty destination, collision, and headroom checks.\"}\n{\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"iteration-3-tree-drift\",\"summary\":\"Supersede scripts/style-library.mjs, scripts/style-database.mjs, and lib/database/oracle.mjs; preserve dual-purpose modules and keep oracle test-owned.\"}\n{\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"generator-baseline-gap\",\"summary\":\"Add backend typecheck and corpus-baseline-v3 targeted test at baseline and mixed-state gates.\"}\n{\"type\":\"correction\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"mutable-database-policy\",\"summary\":\"No sk-design ignore or mutable DB exists; ignore database/* except README and probe style-library.sqlite.current.json.\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":5,\"id\":\"documentation-link-inventory\",\"summary\":\"Rewrite the 1,290 root-relative styles README links plus active skill, catalog, playbook, mode, generator, and packet docs.\"}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Chunked or per-source bundle moves\",\"reason\":\"The one-process argv is far below ARG_MAX and avoids additional partial-failure boundaries and ordering complexity.\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":8,"totalLines":8,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-005.jsonl","time":{"start":1784618994193,"end":1784618994216}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a8124b415486d47016a5f1ff20c4c8191b9970bc6b321e550"}},"id":"prt_f8394ca0f001RQMkgLXEJh5gHS","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f839482f500141Fmcpe2hr0dEH"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784618994220,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ex4yJj7CBgJOnvxpOH7ayEv2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-005.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-005.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 5: Final Conformance Audit and Adjudication\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: \n5: Adversarially audit the target tree and migration plan against tracked inventory, executable consumers, test entrypoints, the manifest-owned bundle set, macOS argument limits, mutable database lifecycle, and iteration-3/4 contradictions. This mandatory fifth iteration adjudicates inputs for later synthesis; it does not synthesize or implement them.\n6: \n7: ## Final Verdict\n8: \n9: The architecture is implementation-ready after four corrections to iteration 4. Retain `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts/`, `database/`, `tests/`, and `docs/`; preserve every production filename one-for-one; move the complete oracle subtree under tests; and add no aliases or speculative wrappers.\n10: \n11: Iteration 4 correctly supersedes iteration 3 on two points:\n12: \n13: 1. Do not create `scripts/style-library.mjs`, `scripts/style-database.mjs`, or `lib/database/oracle.mjs`. `style-library.mjs` and `operator.mjs` already expose callable APIs and guarded direct execution, while every oracle importer is test-owned. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:9-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs:22-29]\n14: 2. Do not use iteration 3's illustrative mutable names. The real default is `style-library.sqlite`, its pointer is `style-library.sqlite.current.json`, and generation files follow `style-library.sqlite.sha256-<hash>.<pid>-<time>.sqlite`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-22] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:1054-1060,1090-1122]\n15: \n16: Iteration 5 corrects iteration 4's incomplete command text: G0 must run the real generator consumer test and typecheck; G3 needs exact-content and destination checks; G4 must probe the actual pointer name and establish an explicit mutable-directory ignore policy. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20]\n17: \n18: ## Confirmed Inventory\n19: \n20: Read-only `git ls-files`, filesystem, manifest, and import audits closed the inventory:\n21: \n22: | Current owner | Confirmed tracked inventory | Destination |\n23: | --- | ---: | --- |\n24: | `_engine/` | 17 files: 9 production modules, 8 test/support files | Modules to `lib/engine/`; `__tests__` to `tests/engine/` |\n25: | `_db/` | 37 files: 8 production modules, 12 test files, 16 oracle files, 1 README | Modules to `lib/database/`; tests to `tests/database/`; oracle to `tests/oracle/`; README to `database/README.md` |\n26: | `_harness/` | 2 files | Script to `scripts/`; README to `docs/extract-refero.md` |\n27: | Root manifests | 2 files | `library/manifests/{crawl-manifest,retrieval-manifest}.json` |\n28: | Bundle roots | 1,290 roots, 7,740 tracked files | Intact six-file units under `library/bundles/<slug>/` |\n29: | Root docs | `README.md`, `manual-testing-playbook.md` | Keep README; move playbook to `docs/` |\n30: \n31: All 17 production modules remain represented:\n32: \n33: - `lib/engine/`: `cards.mjs`, `corpus-use-proof.mjs`, `eligibility.mjs`, `hydrate.mjs`, `manifest.mjs`, `ordering.mjs`, `persistent-adapter.mjs`, `rank-fts.mjs`, `style-library.mjs`.\n34: - `lib/database/`: `canonical.mjs`, `generation-manifest.mjs`, `indexer.mjs`, `operator.mjs`, `retrieval.mjs`, `schema.mjs`, `stage-telemetry.mjs`, `vectors.mjs`.\n35: \n36: Every manifest slug exists, is unique and safe, and owns exactly six tracked artifacts. The styles tree has 7,800 tracked files total: 7,740 bundle files plus 60 source, test, oracle, harness, manifest, and documentation files. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:5-12]\n37: \n38: ## Final Target Tree\n39: \n40: ```text\n41: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/\n42: |-- README.md\n43: |-- library/\n44: |   |-- bundles/\n45: |   |   `-- <1,290-style-slugs>/\n46: |   |       |-- DESIGN.md\n47: |   |       |-- css-variables.css\n48: |   |       |-- tailwind-v4.css\n49: |   |       |-- design-tokens.json\n50: |   |       |-- <style-slug>-canonical.json\n51: |   |       `-- source.md\n52: |   `-- manifests/\n53: |       |-- crawl-manifest.json\n54: |       `-- retrieval-manifest.json\n55: |-- lib/\n56: |   |-- paths.mjs\n57: |   |-- engine/\n58: |   |   |-- cards.mjs\n59: |   |   |-- corpus-use-proof.mjs\n60: |   |   |-- eligibility.mjs\n61: |   |   |-- hydrate.mjs\n62: |   |   |-- manifest.mjs\n63: |   |   |-- ordering.mjs\n64: |   |   |-- persistent-adapter.mjs\n65: |   |   |-- rank-fts.mjs\n66: |   |   `-- style-library.mjs\n67: |   `-- database/\n68: |       |-- canonical.mjs\n69: |       |-- generation-manifest.mjs\n70: |       |-- indexer.mjs\n71: |       |-- operator.mjs\n72: |       |-- retrieval.mjs\n73: |       |-- schema.mjs\n74: |       |-- stage-telemetry.mjs\n75: |       `-- vectors.mjs\n76: |-- scripts/\n77: |   `-- extract-refero.mjs\n78: |-- database/\n79: |   |-- README.md\n80: |   `-- <ignored mutable publication files>\n81: |-- tests/\n82: |   |-- engine/\n83: |   |-- database/\n84: |   `-- oracle/\n85: `-- docs/\n86:     |-- extract-refero.md\n87:     `-- manual-testing-playbook.md\n88: ```\n89: \n90: `lib/paths.mjs` is the only new source module. It exports independent styles-root, bundle-root, crawl-manifest, retrieval-manifest, and database-root defaults while APIs retain explicit overrides. No `backend/`, `runtime/`, `src/`, compatibility tree, or duplicate CLI layer is justified. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:34-36,76-83,120-127]\n91: \n92: ## Consumers and Tests\n93: \n94: The production cutover consumers are the four mode modules plus generator `study-prepare.ts`. The mode modules import `style-library.mjs`; `study-prepare.ts` positionally derives both executable and retrieval manifest. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs:24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-91]\n95: \n96: The four mode suites import engine modules and shared engine fixtures directly, so they belong in G2. Engine and database aggregate runners are real and enumerate six and ten tests respectively. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs:5-10] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/index.mjs:5-14]\n97: \n98: Active documentation requiring path updates includes root `sk-design/README.md`, `SKILL.md`, styles/database/harness docs, feature catalog, both manual-testing-playbook surfaces, mode corpus docs, generator docs, and active packet docs. The styles README contains 1,290 root-relative bundle links; each must become `library/bundles/<slug>/`. Historical changelogs and archived specs may retain old paths only as clearly historical statements. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:21-31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:215-226]\n99: \n100: ## Adjudicated Migration\n101: \n102: ```text\n103: G0 scoped-clean baseline and complete green tests\n104:   -> G1 add paths.mjs and independent overrides, defaults still old\n105:        [MIXED A: old locations, decoupled path API]\n106:   -> G2 move 17 modules, tests, oracle, harness, and docs;\n107:        update internal imports, four modes/tests, and generator\n108:        [MIXED B: new code tree, old bundles/manifests]\n109:   -> G3 preflight and move 1,290 bundles in one git-mv argv;\n110:        move manifests; flip defaults and extractor outputs\n111:        [TARGET: new source and committed-data ownership]\n112:   -> G4 add database ignore policy; update active docs/links;\n113:        run classified stale-path and inventory sweeps\n114:   -> G5 full verification, targeted staging, rename review,\n115:        one migration commit\n116: ```\n117: \n118: Retain iteration 4's exact G2 source lists because they equal the confirmed 9+8 modules. Move test and oracle subtrees only after scoped status is clean; never move `_db` wholesale. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:68-92]\n119: \n120: ## Corrected Test Gates\n121: \n122: Iteration 4's engine, database, and mode commands are real, but G0 omitted the generator test promised by its prose. Use:\n123: \n124: ```bash\n125: set -euo pipefail\n126: ROOT='.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles'\n127: GEN='.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend'\n128: \n129: node \"$ROOT/_engine/style-library.mjs\" build --check\n130: node \"$ROOT/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs\"\n131: node \"$ROOT/_db/__tests__/index.mjs\"\n132: node --test \\\n133:   .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs \\\n134:   .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs \\\n135:   .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs \\\n136:   .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs\n137: npm --prefix \"$GEN\" run typecheck\n138: npm --prefix \"$GEN\" test -- tests/corpus-baseline-v3.test.ts\n139: ```\n140: \n141: After G2, use `node \"$ROOT/tests/engine/index.mjs\"` and `node \"$ROOT/tests/database/index.mjs\"`, then rerun mode suites, generator typecheck, and targeted generator test. G5 additionally runs the full generator suite with `npm --prefix \"$GEN\" test`, build/query/hydrate smoke tests, and persistent `status` without creating a database. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:75-79,134-147]\n142: \n143: ## Shell-Safe Bundle Move\n144: \n145: Retain one process rather than chunks or 1,290 subprocesses. The measured argv payload is 57,205 bytes, longest slug 56 bytes, and host `ARG_MAX` is 1,048,576. One `spawnSync` avoids shell expansion and minimizes partial-failure boundaries.\n146: \n147: Correct iteration 4's preflight by proving exact six-file contents, no untracked passengers, empty destination, no collisions, and conservative argv headroom:\n148: \n149: ```bash\n150: mkdir -p \"$ROOT/library/bundles\" \"$ROOT/library/manifests\"\n151: node --input-type=module <<'NODE'\n152: import fs from 'node:fs';\n153: import path from 'node:path';\n154: import { execFileSync, spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n155: \n156: const root = '.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles';\n157: const destination = path.join(root, 'library/bundles');\n158: const manifest = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path.join(root, '_retrieval-manifest.json'), 'utf8'));\n159: const slugs = manifest.styles.map(({ slug }) => slug).sort();\n160: if (manifest.recordCount !== 1290 || slugs.length !== 1290 || new Set(slugs).size !== 1290) {\n161:   throw new Error('Refusing move: expected exactly 1,290 unique records.');\n162: }\n163: if (!fs.statSync(destination, { throwIfNoEntry: false })?.isDirectory()\n164:     || fs.readdirSync(destination).length !== 0) {\n165:   throw new Error(`Refusing move: destination must exist and be empty: ${destination}`);\n166: }\n167: const tracked = new Set(execFileSync('git', ['ls-files', '-z', '--', root], { encoding: 'utf8' })\n168:   .split('\\0').filter(Boolean));\n169: for (const slug of slugs) {\n170:   if (!/^[a-z0-9]+(?:-[a-z0-9]+)*$/.test(slug)) throw new Error(`Unsafe slug: ${slug}`);\n171:   const source = path.join(root, slug);\n172:   const expected = ['DESIGN.md', 'css-variables.css', 'tailwind-v4.css',\n173:     'design-tokens.json', `${slug}-canonical.json`, 'source.md'].sort();\n174:   const actual = fs.readdirSync(source).sort();\n175:   if (JSON.stringify(actual) !== JSON.stringify(expected)\n176:       || expected.some((name) => !tracked.has(path.join(source, name)))) {\n177:     throw new Error(`Non-canonical bundle: ${source}`);\n178:   }\n179:   if (fs.existsSync(path.join(destination, slug))) throw new Error(`Collision: ${slug}`);\n180: }\n181: const args = ['mv', '--', ...slugs.map((slug) => path.join(root, slug)), destination];\n182: const argvBytes = args.reduce((sum, value) => sum + Buffer.byteLength(value) + 1, 0);\n183: const environmentBytes = Object.entries(process.env)\n184:   .reduce((sum, [key, value]) => sum + Buffer.byteLength(`${key}=${value ?? ''}`) + 1, 0);\n185: const argMax = Number(execFileSync('getconf', ['ARG_MAX'], { encoding: 'utf8' }).trim());\n186: if (argvBytes + environmentBytes >= Math.floor(argMax / 2)) {\n187:   throw new Error('Conservative argv headroom check failed.');\n188: }\n189: const result = spawnSync('git', args, { stdio: 'inherit' });\n190: if (result.error) throw result.error;\n191: if (result.status !== 0) process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n192: NODE\n193: git mv -- \"$ROOT/_manifest.json\" \"$ROOT/library/manifests/crawl-manifest.json\"\n194: git mv -- \"$ROOT/_retrieval-manifest.json\" \"$ROOT/library/manifests/retrieval-manifest.json\"\n195: ```\n196: \n197: `git mv` is not transactional. On nonzero exit, stop, inspect `git status --short -- \"$ROOT\"`, and restore only manifest-enumerated source/destination pairs with operator confirmation. Do not rerun blindly, reset, clean, stash, or broaden paths. After commit, rollback remains `git revert <migration-commit>` plus the old-path baseline. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:168-170]\n198: \n199: ## Mutable Database Policy\n200: \n201: No mutable database file currently exists under `_db`, and `.gitignore` has no sk-design rule. Create only `database/README.md` during source migration and add:\n202: \n203: ```gitignore\n204: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/database/*\n205: !.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/database/README.md\n206: ```\n207: \n208: This lifecycle-wide rule ignores logical databases, generations, pointers, build files, sidecars, temporary pointers, and future optional publication artifacts without implying any should be committed. Probe real names without creating files:\n209: \n210: ```bash\n211: git check-ignore -v \\\n212:   \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite\" \\\n213:   \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite-wal\" \\\n214:   \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite.current.json\" \\\n215:   \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite.sha256-probe.1-1.sqlite\"\n216: git check-ignore -q \"$ROOT/database/README.md\" && exit 1 || true\n217: ```\n218: \n219: Do not move old state, fallback-search it, or build a replacement. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-22] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-10,34-35,251]\n220: \n221: ## Adjudications\n222: \n223: 1. Retain `library/` data versus `lib/` source and one `paths.mjs` seam.\n224: 2. Retain one manifest-derived `git mv` argv after exact-content, destination, and headroom checks.\n225: 3. Supersede iteration 3 wrappers; preserve all 17 module names and contracts.\n226: 4. Supersede iteration 3 production oracle; move all 16 oracle files to tests.\n227: 5. Correct iteration 4 with generator typecheck and baseline test.\n228: 6. Correct iteration 4 with a mutable-directory ignore and actual pointer probe.\n229: 7. Expand iteration 4 to enumerate 1,290 README links and active path docs.\n230: \n231: ## Ruled Out\n232: \n233: - Chunked, `xargs`, wildcard, shell-expanded, or per-bundle moves: unnecessary under measured limits and add failure boundaries.\n234: - Whole backend subtree moves: preserve false ownership and may carry ignored state.\n235: - New wrappers or production oracle code: contradicted by exports and importers.\n236: - Committed example database artifacts: mutable and rebuildable.\n237: - Fixture-local manifest renames: fixtures intentionally exercise explicit paths.\n238: - Aliases, old-database fallback, or database creation: no concrete consumer justifies them.\n239: \n240: ## Sources Consulted\n241: \n242: - Canonical lineage state, strategy, iterations 3-4, and iteration-4 delta.\n243: - Tracked `_engine`, `_db`, `_harness`, manifest, and bundle inventories.\n244: - Four mode corpus production/test trees.\n245: - Generator backend package, `study-prepare.ts`, and baseline test.\n246: - Database schema, indexer, generation-manifest, and operator modules.\n247: - `.gitignore`, scoped `git ls-files`, scoped `git status`, Grep/Glob inventories, and `getconf ARG_MAX`.\n248: \n249: ## Assessment\n250: \n251: - New information ratio: 0.44\n252: - Novelty justification: Three findings are new corrections (measured argv safety, missing generator gate, absent mutable-state ignores); four adjudications consolidate or sharpen prior evidence.\n253: - Questions addressed: all five charter questions, audited rather than reopened.\n254: - Questions answered: all five remain answered; no unresolved architecture question remains.\n255: - Findings count: 7 adjudications.\n256: - Confidence: High for inventory, ownership, consumers, argument safety, test entrypoints, and mutable-state policy. Implementation must still establish a clean scoped baseline.\n257: - Status: complete.\n258: \n259: ## Reflection\n260: \n261: - Worked: closed-set Git classification, exact imports, manifest/filesystem comparison, and real test-runner reads exposed prose omissions.\n262: - Failed: broad old-path searches include historical specs and generated research; implementation must classify active versus historical matches.\n263: - Ruled out: wrappers, production oracle, chunked moves, whole-directory moves, aliases, and database creation remain exhausted.\n264: \n265: ## Recommended Next Focus\n266: \n267: Stop at the configured maximum and hand these adjudicated findings to command-owned synthesis. Do not implement, reduce state, save memory, or migrate source from this iteration.\n\n(End of file - total 267 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 5: Final Conformance Audit and Adjudication\n\n## Focus\n\nAdversarially audit the target tree and migration plan against tracked inventory, executable consumers, test entrypoints, the manifest-owned bundle set, macOS argument limits, mutable database lifecycle, and iteration-3/4 contradictions. This mandatory fifth iteration adjudicates inputs for later synthesis; it does not synthesize or implement them.\n\n## Final Verdict\n\nThe architecture is implementation-ready after four corrections to iteration 4. Retain `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts/`, `database/`, `tests/`, and `docs/`; preserve every production filename one-for-one; move the complete oracle subtree under tests; and add no aliases or speculative wrappers.\n\nIteration 4 correctly supersedes iteration 3 on two points:\n\n1. Do not create `scripts/style-library.mjs`, `scripts/style-database.mjs`, or `lib/database/oracle.mjs`. `style-library.mjs` and `operator.mjs` already expose callable APIs and guarded direct execution, while every oracle importer is test-owned. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:9-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs:22-29]\n2. Do not use iteration 3's illustrative mutable names. The real default is `style-library.sqlite`, its pointer is `style-library.sqlite.current.json`, and generation files follow `style-library.sqlite.sha256-<hash>.<pid>-<time>.sqlite`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-22] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:1054-1060,1090-1122]\n\nIteration 5 corrects iteration 4's incomplete command text: G0 must run the real generator consumer test and typecheck; G3 needs exact-content and destination checks; G4 must probe the actual pointer name and establish an explicit mutable-directory ignore policy. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20]\n\n## Confirmed Inventory\n\nRead-only `git ls-files`, filesystem, manifest, and import audits closed the inventory:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-005.md","text":"# Iteration 5: Final Conformance Audit and Adjudication\n\n## Focus\n\nAdversarially audit the target tree and migration plan against tracked inventory, executable consumers, test entrypoints, the manifest-owned bundle set, macOS argument limits, mutable database lifecycle, and iteration-3/4 contradictions. This mandatory fifth iteration adjudicates inputs for later synthesis; it does not synthesize or implement them.\n\n## Final Verdict\n\nThe architecture is implementation-ready after four corrections to iteration 4. Retain `library/{bundles,manifests}`, `lib/{engine,database}`, `scripts/`, `database/`, `tests/`, and `docs/`; preserve every production filename one-for-one; move the complete oracle subtree under tests; and add no aliases or speculative wrappers.\n\nIteration 4 correctly supersedes iteration 3 on two points:\n\n1. Do not create `scripts/style-library.mjs`, `scripts/style-database.mjs`, or `lib/database/oracle.mjs`. `style-library.mjs` and `operator.mjs` already expose callable APIs and guarded direct execution, while every oracle importer is test-owned. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:9-16] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs:22-29]\n2. Do not use iteration 3's illustrative mutable names. The real default is `style-library.sqlite`, its pointer is `style-library.sqlite.current.json`, and generation files follow `style-library.sqlite.sha256-<hash>.<pid>-<time>.sqlite`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-22] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs:1054-1060,1090-1122]\n\nIteration 5 corrects iteration 4's incomplete command text: G0 must run the real generator consumer test and typecheck; G3 needs exact-content and destination checks; G4 must probe the actual pointer name and establish an explicit mutable-directory ignore policy. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20]\n\n## Confirmed Inventory\n\nRead-only `git ls-files`, filesystem, manifest, and import audits closed the inventory:\n\n| Current owner | Confirmed tracked inventory | Destination |\n| --- | ---: | --- |\n| `_engine/` | 17 files: 9 production modules, 8 test/support files | Modules to `lib/engine/`; `__tests__` to `tests/engine/` |\n| `_db/` | 37 files: 8 production modules, 12 test files, 16 oracle files, 1 README | Modules to `lib/database/`; tests to `tests/database/`; oracle to `tests/oracle/`; README to `database/README.md` |\n| `_harness/` | 2 files | Script to `scripts/`; README to `docs/extract-refero.md` |\n| Root manifests | 2 files | `library/manifests/{crawl-manifest,retrieval-manifest}.json` |\n| Bundle roots | 1,290 roots, 7,740 tracked files | Intact six-file units under `library/bundles/<slug>/` |\n| Root docs | `README.md`, `manual-testing-playbook.md` | Keep README; move playbook to `docs/` |\n\nAll 17 production modules remain represented:\n\n- `lib/engine/`: `cards.mjs`, `corpus-use-proof.mjs`, `eligibility.mjs`, `hydrate.mjs`, `manifest.mjs`, `ordering.mjs`, `persistent-adapter.mjs`, `rank-fts.mjs`, `style-library.mjs`.\n- `lib/database/`: `canonical.mjs`, `generation-manifest.mjs`, `indexer.mjs`, `operator.mjs`, `retrieval.mjs`, `schema.mjs`, `stage-telemetry.mjs`, `vectors.mjs`.\n\nEvery manifest slug exists, is unique and safe, and owns exactly six tracked artifacts. The styles tree has 7,800 tracked files total: 7,740 bundle files plus 60 source, test, oracle, harness, manifest, and documentation files. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:5-12]\n\n## Final Target Tree\n\n```text\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/\n|-- README.md\n|-- library/\n|   |-- bundles/\n|   |   `-- <1,290-style-slugs>/\n|   |       |-- DESIGN.md\n|   |       |-- css-variables.css\n|   |       |-- tailwind-v4.css\n|   |       |-- design-tokens.json\n|   |       |-- <style-slug>-canonical.json\n|   |       `-- source.md\n|   `-- manifests/\n|       |-- crawl-manifest.json\n|       `-- retrieval-manifest.json\n|-- lib/\n|   |-- paths.mjs\n|   |-- engine/\n|   |   |-- cards.mjs\n|   |   |-- corpus-use-proof.mjs\n|   |   |-- eligibility.mjs\n|   |   |-- hydrate.mjs\n|   |   |-- manifest.mjs\n|   |   |-- ordering.mjs\n|   |   |-- persistent-adapter.mjs\n|   |   |-- rank-fts.mjs\n|   |   `-- style-library.mjs\n|   `-- database/\n|       |-- canonical.mjs\n|       |-- generation-manifest.mjs\n|       |-- indexer.mjs\n|       |-- operator.mjs\n|       |-- retrieval.mjs\n|       |-- schema.mjs\n|       |-- stage-telemetry.mjs\n|       `-- vectors.mjs\n|-- scripts/\n|   `-- extract-refero.mjs\n|-- database/\n|   |-- README.md\n|   `-- <ignored mutable publication files>\n|-- tests/\n|   |-- engine/\n|   |-- database/\n|   `-- oracle/\n`-- docs/\n    |-- extract-refero.md\n    `-- manual-testing-playbook.md\n```\n\n`lib/paths.mjs` is the only new source module. It exports independent styles-root, bundle-root, crawl-manifest, retrieval-manifest, and database-root defaults while APIs retain explicit overrides. No `backend/`, `runtime/`, `src/`, compatibility tree, or duplicate CLI layer is justified. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:34-36,76-83,120-127]\n\n## Consumers and Tests\n\nThe production cutover consumers are the four mode modules plus generator `study-prepare.ts`. The mode modules import `style-library.mjs`; `study-prepare.ts` positionally derives both executable and retrieval manifest. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs:24] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:28] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/scripts/study-prepare.ts:54-91]\n\nThe four mode suites import engine modules and shared engine fixtures directly, so they belong in G2. Engine and database aggregate runners are real and enumerate six and ten tests respectively. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs:5-10] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/index.mjs:5-14]\n\nActive documentation requiring path updates includes root `sk-design/README.md`, `SKILL.md`, styles/database/harness docs, feature catalog, both manual-testing-playbook surfaces, mode corpus docs, generator docs, and active packet docs. The styles README contains 1,290 root-relative bundle links; each must become `library/bundles/<slug>/`. Historical changelogs and archived specs may retain old paths only as clearly historical statements. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/README.md:21-31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:215-226]\n\n## Adjudicated Migration\n\n```text\nG0 scoped-clean baseline and complete green tests\n  -> G1 add paths.mjs and independent overrides, defaults still old\n       [MIXED A: old locations, decoupled path API]\n  -> G2 move 17 modules, tests, oracle, harness, and docs;\n       update internal imports, four modes/tests, and generator\n       [MIXED B: new code tree, old bundles/manifests]\n  -> G3 preflight and move 1,290 bundles in one git-mv argv;\n       move manifests; flip defaults and extractor outputs\n       [TARGET: new source and committed-data ownership]\n  -> G4 add database ignore policy; update active docs/links;\n       run classified stale-path and inventory sweeps\n  -> G5 full verification, targeted staging, rename review,\n       one migration commit\n```\n\nRetain iteration 4's exact G2 source lists because they equal the confirmed 9+8 modules. Move test and oracle subtrees only after scoped status is clean; never move `_db` wholesale. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:68-92]\n\n## Corrected Test Gates\n\nIteration 4's engine, database, and mode commands are real, but G0 omitted the generator test promised by its prose. Use:\n\n```bash\nset -euo pipefail\nROOT='.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles'\nGEN='.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend'\n\nnode \"$ROOT/_engine/style-library.mjs\" build --check\nnode \"$ROOT/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs\"\nnode \"$ROOT/_db/__tests__/index.mjs\"\nnode --test \\\n  .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs \\\n  .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs \\\n  .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs \\\n  .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/__tests__/*.test.mjs\nnpm --prefix \"$GEN\" run typecheck\nnpm --prefix \"$GEN\" test -- tests/corpus-baseline-v3.test.ts\n```\n\nAfter G2, use `node \"$ROOT/tests/engine/index.mjs\"` and `node \"$ROOT/tests/database/index.mjs\"`, then rerun mode suites, generator typecheck, and targeted generator test. G5 additionally runs the full generator suite with `npm --prefix \"$GEN\" test`, build/query/hydrate smoke tests, and persistent `status` without creating a database. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/backend/package.json:13-20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md:75-79,134-147]\n\n## Shell-Safe Bundle Move\n\nRetain one process rather than chunks or 1,290 subprocesses. The measured argv payload is 57,205 bytes, longest slug 56 bytes, and host `ARG_MAX` is 1,048,576. One `spawnSync` avoids shell expansion and minimizes partial-failure boundaries.\n\nCorrect iteration 4's preflight by proving exact six-file contents, no untracked passengers, empty destination, no collisions, and conservative argv headroom:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"$ROOT/library/bundles\" \"$ROOT/library/manifests\"\nnode --input-type=module <<'NODE'\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport { execFileSync, spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\nconst root = '.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles';\nconst destination = path.join(root, 'library/bundles');\nconst manifest = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path.join(root, '_retrieval-manifest.json'), 'utf8'));\nconst slugs = manifest.styles.map(({ slug }) => slug).sort();\nif (manifest.recordCount !== 1290 || slugs.length !== 1290 || new Set(slugs).size !== 1290) {\n  throw new Error('Refusing move: expected exactly 1,290 unique records.');\n}\nif (!fs.statSync(destination, { throwIfNoEntry: false })?.isDirectory()\n    || fs.readdirSync(destination).length !== 0) {\n  throw new Error(`Refusing move: destination must exist and be empty: ${destination}`);\n}\nconst tracked = new Set(execFileSync('git', ['ls-files', '-z', '--', root], { encoding: 'utf8' })\n  .split('\\0').filter(Boolean));\nfor (const slug of slugs) {\n  if (!/^[a-z0-9]+(?:-[a-z0-9]+)*$/.test(slug)) throw new Error(`Unsafe slug: ${slug}`);\n  const source = path.join(root, slug);\n  const expected = ['DESIGN.md', 'css-variables.css', 'tailwind-v4.css',\n    'design-tokens.json', `${slug}-canonical.json`, 'source.md'].sort();\n  const actual = fs.readdirSync(source).sort();\n  if (JSON.stringify(actual) !== JSON.stringify(expected)\n      || expected.some((name) => !tracked.has(path.join(source, name)))) {\n    throw new Error(`Non-canonical bundle: ${source}`);\n  }\n  if (fs.existsSync(path.join(destination, slug))) throw new Error(`Collision: ${slug}`);\n}\nconst args = ['mv', '--', ...slugs.map((slug) => path.join(root, slug)), destination];\nconst argvBytes = args.reduce((sum, value) => sum + Buffer.byteLength(value) + 1, 0);\nconst environmentBytes = Object.entries(process.env)\n  .reduce((sum, [key, value]) => sum + Buffer.byteLength(`${key}=${value ?? ''}`) + 1, 0);\nconst argMax = Number(execFileSync('getconf', ['ARG_MAX'], { encoding: 'utf8' }).trim());\nif (argvBytes + environmentBytes >= Math.floor(argMax / 2)) {\n  throw new Error('Conservative argv headroom check failed.');\n}\nconst result = spawnSync('git', args, { stdio: 'inherit' });\nif (result.error) throw result.error;\nif (result.status !== 0) process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\nNODE\ngit mv -- \"$ROOT/_manifest.json\" \"$ROOT/library/manifests/crawl-manifest.json\"\ngit mv -- \"$ROOT/_retrieval-manifest.json\" \"$ROOT/library/manifests/retrieval-manifest.json\"\n```\n\n`git mv` is not transactional. On nonzero exit, stop, inspect `git status --short -- \"$ROOT\"`, and restore only manifest-enumerated source/destination pairs with operator confirmation. Do not rerun blindly, reset, clean, stash, or broaden paths. After commit, rollback remains `git revert <migration-commit>` plus the old-path baseline. [SOURCE: iterations/iteration-004.md:168-170]\n\n## Mutable Database Policy\n\nNo mutable database file currently exists under `_db`, and `.gitignore` has no sk-design rule. Create only `database/README.md` during source migration and add:\n\n```gitignore\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/database/*\n!.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/database/README.md\n```\n\nThis lifecycle-wide rule ignores logical databases, generations, pointers, build files, sidecars, temporary pointers, and future optional publication artifacts without implying any should be committed. Probe real names without creating files:\n\n```bash\ngit check-ignore -v \\\n  \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite\" \\\n  \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite-wal\" \\\n  \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite.current.json\" \\\n  \"$ROOT/database/style-library.sqlite.sha256-probe.1-1.sqlite\"\ngit check-ignore -q \"$ROOT/database/README.md\" && exit 1 || true\n```\n\nDo not move old state, fallback-search it, or build a replacement. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/schema.mjs:11-22] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs:5-10,34-35,251]\n\n## Adjudications\n\n1. Retain `library/` data versus `lib/` source and one `paths.mjs` seam.\n2. Retain one manifest-derived `git mv` argv after exact-content, destination, and headroom checks.\n3. Supersede iteration 3 wrappers; preserve all 17 module names and contracts.\n4. Supersede iteration 3 production oracle; move all 16 oracle files to tests.\n5. Correct iteration 4 with generator typecheck and baseline test.\n6. Correct iteration 4 with a mutable-directory ignore and actual pointer probe.\n7. Expand iteration 4 to enumerate 1,290 README links and active path docs.\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Chunked, `xargs`, wildcard, shell-expanded, or per-bundle moves: unnecessary under measured limits and add failure boundaries.\n- Whole backend subtree moves: preserve false ownership and may carry ignored state.\n- New wrappers or production oracle code: contradicted by exports and importers.\n- Committed example database artifacts: mutable and rebuildable.\n- Fixture-local manifest renames: fixtures intentionally exercise explicit paths.\n- Aliases, old-database fallback, or database creation: no concrete consumer justifies them.\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- Canonical lineage state, strategy, iterations 3-4, and iteration-4 delta.\n- Tracked `_engine`, `_db`, `_harness`, manifest, and bundle inventories.\n- Four mode corpus production/test trees.\n- Generator backend package, `study-prepare.ts`, and baseline test.\n- Database schema, indexer, generation-manifest, and operator modules.\n- `.gitignore`, scoped `git ls-files`, scoped `git status`, Grep/Glob inventories, and `getconf ARG_MAX`.\n\n## Assessment\n\n- New information ratio: 0.44\n- Novelty justification: Three findings are new corrections (measured argv safety, missing generator gate, absent mutable-state ignores); four adjudications consolidate or sharpen prior evidence.\n- Questions addressed: all five charter questions, audited rather than reopened.\n- Questions answered: all five remain answered; no unresolved architecture question remains.\n- Findings count: 7 adjudications.\n- Confidence: High for inventory, ownership, consumers, argument safety, test entrypoints, and mutable-state policy. Implementation must still establish a clean scoped baseline.\n- Status: complete.\n\n## Reflection\n\n- Worked: closed-set Git classification, exact imports, manifest/filesystem comparison, and real test-runner reads exposed prose omissions.\n- Failed: broad old-path searches include historical specs and generated research; implementation must classify active versus historical matches.\n- Ruled out: wrappers, production oracle, chunked moves, whole-directory moves, aliases, and database creation remain exhausted.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nStop at the configured maximum and hand these adjudicated findings to command-owned synthesis. Do not implement, reduce state, save memory, or migrate source from this iteration.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":267,"totalLines":267,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/001-restructure/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-005.md","time":{"start":1784618994190,"end":1784618994218}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a8124b415486d47016a5f1ff20c348191a498b113d03bbc8a"}},"id":"prt_f8394c9c7001GqH1r0nhqbWxco","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f839482f500141Fmcpe2hr0dEH"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784618994722,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"id":"prt_f8394cc1f001xB0ZiTb91Sna9z","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"2916bdc04951e6884fd78265f3de62007f8dc809","messageID":"msg_f839482f500141Fmcpe2hr0dEH","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":92777,"input":1291,"output":346,"reasoning":516,"cache":{"write":0,"read":90624}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784619003168,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"id":"prt_f8394ed15001FZHyckiz135mGx","messageID":"msg_f8394ce46001i7CLw9X0qJwPoD","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","snapshot":"2916bdc04951e6884fd78265f3de62007f8dc809","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784619005138,"sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tSnaJq9RViglXySj8sRQ1PwJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md","offset":520,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n520: - Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n521: \n522: **Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n523: \n524: ---\n525: \n526: ## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n527: \n528: ### Purpose\n529: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n530: \n531: ### Steps\n532: \n533: 1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n534: 2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n535: 3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n536:    - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n537:    - Organize by section topic\n538:    - Add citations from iteration files\n539:    - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n540:    - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n541:    - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n542:    - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n543:      - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n544:      - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n545:      - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n546:      - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n547:      - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n548:      - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n549: 4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n550: 5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n551: 6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n552: \n553: ### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n554: - If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n555: - If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n560: \n561: ### Purpose\n562: Preserve research context to memory system.\n563: \n564: ### Steps\n565: \n566: 1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n567: 2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n568: 3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n573: \n574: ```text\n575: [INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n576:     |\n577: [ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n578:     |\n579: [EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n580:     |\n581:     |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n582:     |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n583:     |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n584: \n585: [STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n586:     |\n587:     |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n588:     |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n589: \n590: [SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n591:     |\n592: [SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n593:     |\n594: [COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n595: ```\n596: \n597: Hook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n602: \n603: | Error | Phase | Action |\n604: |-------|-------|--------|\n605: | Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n606: | WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n607: | State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n608: | JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n609: | 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n610: | Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n611: | Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n612: \n613: ### State Recovery Protocol\n614: \n615: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n616: \n617: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n618: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n619: | 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n620: | 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n621: | 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n622: | 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n623: | 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n624: \n625: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state-format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n626: \n627: ---\n628: \n629: ## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n\n(Showing lines 520-629 of 646. Use offset=630 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n\n**Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\nCompile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n   - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n   - Organize by section topic\n   - Add citations from iteration files\n   - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md","text":"- Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n\n**Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\nCompile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n   - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n   - Organize by section topic\n   - Add citations from iteration files\n   - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n   - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n   - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n   - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n     - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n     - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n     - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n     - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n     - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n     - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n\n### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\nPreserve research context to memory system.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n```text\n[INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n    |\n[ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n    |\n[EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n    |\n    |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n    |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n\n[STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n    |\n    |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n\n[SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n    |\n[SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n    |\n[COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n```\n\nHook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n\n---\n\n## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Error | Phase | Action |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n| WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n| State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n| JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n| Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n\n### State Recovery Protocol\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n| 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n| 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n| 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state-format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n\n---\n\n## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS","lineStart":520,"lineEnd":629,"totalLines":646,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md","time":{"start":1784619005131,"end":1784619005137}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09e2306df15085d9016a5f1ffc05288191bcaa1f7ef68745c8"}},"id":"prt_f8394f186001mWmRppX1pOPz0m","sessionID":"ses_07c97d905ffee2yzbow793KIc8","messageID":"msg_f8394ce46001i7CLw9X0qJwPoD"}}
