oritative corpus and committed corpus manifests that runtime does not own.\n130: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n131: - Do NOT retry: Ruled out a literal mirror of runtime directory names: styles requires an authoritative corpus and committed corpus manifests that runtime does not own.\n132: \n133: ### Ruled out a top-level `manifests/`: both committed files are metadata for `library/`, whereas generation metadata belongs to `database/`; a shared manifest root would merge lifecycles again. -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempts)\n134: - What was tried: Ruled out a top-level `manifests/`: both committed files are metadata for `library/`, whereas generation metadata belongs to `database/`; a shared manifest root would merge lifecycles again.\n135: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n136: - Do NOT retry: Ruled out a top-level `manifests/`: both committed files are metadata for `library/`, whereas generation metadata belongs to `database/`; a shared manifest root would merge lifecycles again.\n137: \n138: ### Ruled out keeping `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` at the styles root: root globals preserve the ownership ambiguity the restructure is intended to remove. -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempts)\n139: - What was tried: Ruled out keeping `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` at the styles root: root globals preserve the ownership ambiguity the restructure is intended to remove.\n140: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n141: - Do NOT retry: Ruled out keeping `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` at the styles root: root globals preserve the ownership ambiguity the restructure is intended to remove.\n142: \n143: ### Ruled out placing `_manifest.json` and `_retrieval-manifest.json` under `database/`: their authority and default-backend lifecycle differ from mutable SQLite publication pointers. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n144: