te |\n36: | 2 | Reference-architecture transfer rules and intentional styles-specific differences. | architecture | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n37: | 3 | Concrete target tree and exact ownership of every current artifact class. | architecture | 0.88 | 8 | complete |\n38: | 4 | Dependency-ordered migration, exact shell-safe git mv plan, compatibility policy, verification ladder, and rollback. | migration | 0.86 | 8 | complete |\n39: | 5 | Final conformance audit, contradiction resolution, inventory completeness, command safety, and implementation-ready adjudication. | audit | 0.44 | 7 | complete |\n40: \n41: - iterationsCompleted: 5\n42: - keyFindings: 33\n43: - openQuestions: 0\n44: - resolvedQuestions: 5\n45: \n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n47: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n48: ## 4. QUESTIONS\n49: - Answered: 5/5\n50: - [x] What is the exact current ownership and dependency topology across style data, engine, database, harness, manifests, tests, docs, and consumers?\n51: - [x] Which parts of system-deep-loop/runtime transfer directly, and where should styles intentionally differ?\n52: - [x] What target layout cleanly separates data, library code, runtime databases, manifests, tests, scripts, and documentation?\n53: - [x] What dependency-ordered migration preserves behavior and avoids a flag day across imports, path constants, fixtures, commands, and docs?\n54: - [x] What exact git mv sequence, verification ladder, rollback boundary, and compatibility policy should implementation use?\n55: \n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n57: <!-- ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n58: ## Uncovered Questions\n59: - Count: 0\n60: - None\n61: \n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:uncovered-questions -->\n63: <!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n64: ## 5. TREND\n65: - newInfoRatio sparkline: ███████████████▇▅▄▂▁\n66: - score sparkline: ███████████████▇▅▄▂▁\n67: - Last 3 ratios: 0.88 -> 0.86 -> 0.44\n68: - Stuck count: 0\n69: - Guard violations: none recorded by the reducer pass\n\n(Showing lines 15-69 of 135. Use offset=70 to